🧄 ~ A G L I O ~ E ~ O L I O ~ 🧄

Simply means Spaghetti with Oil & Garlic. This is such a simple but beautifully delicate & delicious dish.

✨ CALLING ALL PASTA LOVERS ✨

Serves 2
Ingredients- 

- 6 tbsp extra Virgin Olive Oil @bertollioliveoiluk for me!
- 8 garlic cloves finely sliced
- 200g pasta- spaghetti or linguine
- Handful fresh parsley, finely chopped
- Salt, 1/2 Tsp
- 1/2 Tsp Black pepper- fresh ground
- Parmesan- (optional 50-80g)

In a pan add cold water heavily salted and bring to a boil. 

In a large non stick frying pan add the oil lightly heat, the key to this dish is to slowly bring the garlic to temperature without burning and allowing it to go lightly golden brown. Add the sliced garlic and ensure it doesn’t sizzle, just a low heat is fine. 

Add the pasta to the salted water and boil.
Once your kitchen smells like an authentic Italian restaurant or my dads kitchen 🧄 (extra garlic on everything) add the cooked pasta directly from the pan so it brings with it the salted pasta water, also add the freshly chopped parsley, salt, pepper & grated parmesan.

Turn off the heat and gently fold the pasta until the liquid emulsifies and goes creamy and delicious, add more pasta water if needed. 

Parmesan isn’t traditional, but sure as hell is an incredible addition and one I wouldn’t miss, especially if you’re having a glass of red with it 🤤🍷🍴

This one is bowl licking good. 

Much Love,
Jade x

Brioche feuilletée de @jimmy_mornet que l’on retrouve dans le magazine @foudepatisserie « à la folie boulangerie ! »

Ingrédients :

30 g de levure boulangère fraîche
60 g de lait entier
800 g de farine T55
15 g de sel fin
105 g de sucre semoule
280 g de blanc d’œuf 
140 g de jaune d’œuf
160 g de beurre doux
400 g de beurre de tourage

J’ai divisé les quantités par 3 et mis 3 œufs.

Mettre le sel (en premier pour qu’il ne soit pas en contact direct avec la levure), recouvrir de farine et sucre dans une cuve à batteur. Ajouter la levure et le lait, puis les œufs mélangés en omelette. 
 
Pétrir la pâte pendant une vingtaine de minutes. 

Ajouter le beurre doux froid coupé en dés en plusieurs fois. Pétrir jusqu’à ce que la pâte se décroche des parois de la cuve. Laisser la pâte pointer une nuit au réfrigérateur.

Le lendemain, rabattre la pâte pour chasser l’air et enfermer le beurre de tourage à l’intérieur. 

Réaliser 3 tours simples sans temps de repos entre chaque tour. Laisser refroidir une heure au réfrigérateur, étaler sur 5 mm et façonner vos brioches en roulant des bandes, en formant des tresses…

La pâte une fois roulée doit avoir un diamètre deux fois inférieure à celui du cercle ou du moule dans lequel vous voulez cuire votre brioche. 

Laisser pousser 2 heures à température ambiante et enfourner à 165° pendant 30 minutes environ. 

Bon dimanche ! Prenez soin de vous. ☺️🥹

HOT & COLD
.
Roasted peppers & tomatoes paired with cool whipped ricotta.
It makes for a sensational pairing 🍅
.
📌  The easiest of easy recipes. Roast your veg with olive oil, garlic cloves, seasalt, pepper, a bit of tomato purée or Turkish red pepper paste if you have it. The residual caramelised juices are perfect spooned over light creamy ricotta cut with a squeeze of lemon juice. Garnish with any fresh herb you like. Bread scoops are a must. We love eating like this at the start of the week - generally both of us are out on a Monday evening doing some form of exercise and dinners like this are quick, tasty and don't feel particularly heavy 🙌🏽

Bonsoir mes "sucrésalé" 🥰
Vous avez passé une bonne journée ?

Aujourd'hui il a fait moins chaud du coup pour le dîner j'ai préparé un risotto cremeux aux courgettes, accompagné des crevettes 🤤
Nous on adore le risotto et j'essaie de le revisité en fonction des légumes de saison 😊
Et vous, aimez-vous les risottos ?

Voici la recette :
1 courgette bio coupée en morceaux 
250 g de riz à risotto bio
1 oignon nouveau émincé 
150 ml de vin blanc
2 c.s d'huile d'olive
70 g de parmesan râpé 
1 litre de bouillon
sel

30 g de graines de courge bio

250 g de crevettes décortiquées
1 gousse d'ail émincé
1 c.s sauce soja sucré
1 c.s d'huile d'olive 
sel, poivre
* ciboulette ciselée 

Faites revenir les graines de courge dans une poêle sans matière grasse pour les grilles légèrement.

Chauffez le bouillon.
Dans votre cocotte faites revenir l'oignon émincé et les morceaux de courgette dans l'huile d'olive.
Ajoutez le riz et poursuivez la cuisson jusqu'à ce qu'il devient translucide (2 minutes). 
Mouillez avec le vin blanc.
Quand il est complètement évaporé commencez à ajouté une louche de bouillon et attendez qu'elle soit évaporée pour ajoutez une deuxième et ainsi de suite jusqu'à ce que votre riz est cuit et il a la consistance souhaitée. N'oubliez pas de mélangez régulièrement,surtout vers la fin de la cuisson sinon ça risque de coller à votre cocotte...
Quand le riz a atteint la consistance souhaitée ajoutez le parmesan et mélangez bien.
Rectifiez l'assaisonnement si nécessaire.

Dans une poêle faites revenir les crevettes avec l'huile d'olive, l'ail émincé et la sauce soja pendant 2-3 minutes, salez et poivrez.

Dans vos assiettes déposez le risotto, quelques crevettes, des graines de courge grillés et parsemez de ciboulette ciselée.

Régalez-vous 😋
C'est trop trop bon 🤤

Belle soirée à vous 💚💚

Roasted Vegetable Lentil Bowl
—————————————————————-
Now the weather has cooled slightly (thank goodness), warmer dishes are back on the menu! 

Ingredients (2-3 servings): 
1 cup of Puy lentils 
1 bay leaf
1 garlic clove 
1 vegetable stock cube
-
1 aubergine 
1 courgette 
1tbsp capers 
1tbsp chopped sun-dried tomatoes
2 cherry tomatoes - chopped 
2tbsp chopped parsley 
30g feta 
1tbsp za’atar 
-
2tbsp extra virgin olive oil 
1tbsp red wine vinegar 
1tsp sumac 

Wash the lentils gently, drain water and place into a saucepan with the bay leaf, crushed garlic clove and veggie stock cube. Fill with 1 cup of water, bring to the boil then turn down to a simmer with a lid on. Cook until the water has absorbed and the lentils are cooked through. 

Meanwhile, heat your oven to 180 degrees. Chop the aubergine and courgette into same size chunks. Coat with 1tbsp of olive oil and the za’atar spices. Roast for 25-30 minutes stirring half way.

Assemble the warm salad with all of the extra ingredients above and dress with a mix of extra virgin olive oil, red wine vinegar and sumac.

This week we are continuing on with another delicious and also healthy Mexican meal plan with our Chicken Tacos, Pico de Gallo and a crunchy and colourful Mexican Bean Salad.⁠
⁠
Click the link in our bio @granluchito or see below for recipe.⁠
⁠
Ingredients - ⁠
Chicken:⁠
500g /1.1 lbs of chicken breasts⁠
2 teaspoons Gran Luchito Smoky Chipotle Fajita and Taco Mix⁠
1 lime (juice)⁠
2 tablespoons olive oil⁠
Salt and freshly ground black pepper (for seasoning)⁠
⁠
Guacamole:⁠
2 ripe avocados⁠
½ red onion (finely diced)⁠
1 jalapeño (finely chopped)⁠
1 tablespoon extra virgin olive oil⁠
⁠
Pico de Gallo:⁠
2 vine tomatoes (diced)⁠
½ red onion (finely diced)⁠
1 tablespoon extra virgin olive oil⁠
1 lime (juice)⁠
1 handful of coriander (roughly chopped)⁠
⁠
To Serve:⁠
6 Gran Luchito Soft Tacos Wraps⁠
⁠
How to make it - ⁠
1. Add the Smoky Chipotle Fajita and Taco Mix onto your chicken breasts with the lime juice, 1 tablespoon of olive oil, a pinch of salt and freshly ground black pepper. Cover with cling film and let it marinate for 20 mins at least.⁠
2. In the meantime prepare a quick guacamole. Add the avocado flesh into a bowl and mash it with a fork. Add the onion, jalapeno, extra virgin olive oil, a pinch of salt and black pepper, then mix and set aside.⁠
3. In a different bowl prepare a quick pico de gallo. Mix the tomatoes, onion, extra virgin olive oil, lime juice, coriander, salt and pepper.⁠
4. Get the barbecue going or heat up a cast-iron skillet with the remaining olive oil. Grill or pan-fry your marinated chicken and let it get a bit of colour on both sides. Finish cooking it covered with a lid, to allow it to cook fully without getting dry.⁠
5. Once ready, remove from the heat and cut the chicken into strips with a sharp knife. Serve your chicken with warm Soft Taco Wraps, a good amount of guacamole and some of the pico de gallo. Finally don’t forget to try some Gran Luchito Salsas!

Utk baking sehari2, selalu gunakan Produk dari @chefmatechocolate ❤️
Kwalitas sdh gak ush diragukan sgt terpercaya dari Produk @chefmatechocolate jgn lupa teman2 cek IG @chefmatechocolate bnyk resep2 menarik dan ada live baking demo tiap hari 😍
----------------------------------------------
BOLU JADUL 3 WARNA
Loyang tulban uk 24x9cm
Oleh: @yulichia88

Bahan:
375 gram mentega (aku blueband dan butter wijsman)
275 gram gula halus KIS @chefmatechocolate
250 gram terigu protein rendah
35 gram susu bubuk
60 gram susu kental manis
Vanili secukupnya
10 kuning telur
4 putih telur
Secukupnya Cocoa Powder @chefmatechocolate pasta mocca, pasta coklat 

Cara:
1. Kocok mentega dan gula halus Kis, vanili hingga mengembang
2. Lalu masukkan kuning telur satu persatu mixer rata, masukkan susu kental manis sambil trus dimixer
3. Masukkan susu bubuk dan terigu yg sdh diayak terlebih dahulu, sambil dimixer rata dgn kecepatan rendah
4. Mixer putih telur hingga mengembang kaku
5. Campur ke adonan kuning diaduk rata menggunakan Spatula 
6. Bagi adonan 3 bagian ( mocca, coklat dan plain) utk adonan mocca, tambahkan 1 sdt terigu dan utk adonan coklat, tambahkan 1sdm Cocoa Powder dan sedikit pasta coklat, lalu tuang ke cetakan( caranya bisa liat di video ya, postingan sebelah ya 👉)
7. Panggang di oven yg sdh dipanaskan terlebih dahulu, suhu awal 160°c api bawah 25 menit lalu set api atas bawah turunkan suhu 150°c  panggang smp matang, tergantung oven masing2 ya, biar aman lakukan test tusuk ya, jika adonan msh menempel di alat tusukan berarti kuenya blm mateng

Petits pains au lait chocolat🍫

Pour 14 petits pains:
-400gr de farine
-100gr de chocolat
-25cl de lait
-60gr de fromage blanc
-2oeufs 
-1CaS de miel
-1sachet de levure boulangère

✳Melange farine+levure+chocolat
✴Fais un puit et ajoute le fromage blanc, le lait, les oeufs et le miel
✴Pétris la pâte, et laisses poser sous un torchon 2h30
✴Dégaze la pâte et forme les boules, dispose sur une plaque allant au four et laisse denouveau poser 1h30
✴Badigeonne de lait et fais cuir 15-20min a 180°C

Total pour un pain 153kcal

~Keema Masala~ Recipe ⬇️

Follow @what_tocook for more delicious recipes.

You need;
500 gm minced beef(boil with 1/4 tsp of salt)
1 Onion paste
4-5 curry leaves 
1 tbsp ginger garlic paste
1 tbsp tomato paste 
1 tomato purée 
1 tsp salt
1 tsp red chilli 
1/4 tsp turmeric 
1 tbsp chilli flakes 
1/2 tsp black pepper 
1 tsp cumin seed
1/4 tsp garam masala 
1 tbsp yogurt 
2 tbsp Kasuri Meethi
Fresh coriander 
Green chillies chopped 

Method;
✨Boil minced meat with 500ml water and salt, boil till water evaporates.keep aside.
✨In a pan add onion paste and curry leaves.
✨Fry until onion changes colour.
✨Add ginger garlic paste, fry for 2 mins.
✨Add tomato paste and tomato purée, with all the spices.
✨Mix, add splash of water so that the masala doesn’t burn.
Add boiled keema, fry for 3-4 mins.
✨Add yogurt and mix
✨In the end add Kasuri meethi, add 1/2 cup water, cover and let it cook for 5 mins of low flame.
Garnish with chopped fresh coriander and green chilies.

Enjoy 😉

Ciccio Pancake proteico agli spinaci 🥞🥬

❌Senza glutine,senza burro,senza olio
✔️High protein,low carb,

Buongiorno!
Oggi di nuovo Ciccio pancake,ma in versione salata con gli spinaci! Ho utilizzato la farina di ceci,quindi una farina senza glutine, ad alto contenuto proteico e ricca di fibre. Come topping invece,ho scelto di abbinarci una crema di mandorle bianca e delle mandorle pelate/sgusciate.
Le dosi che ho utilizzato sono le stesse di quando avevo fatto i pancake.
A voi la scelta,se suddividere il composto in più parti o decidere di fare un Ciccio pancake semplicemente versando il tutto in un pentolino antiaderente!
Se siete curiosi di sapere come ho realizzato il tutto,vi lascio qui sotto 👇🏻 gli ingredienti e nei commenti,il procedimento!

Ingredienti

100 g farina di ceci @molinospadoni 
100 g spinaci
100 ml albume
35 ml acqua
10 g parmigiano grattugiato
3 g idrolitina
5 g lievito istantaneo 

Top

15 g crema di mandorle bianca @probios1978 
15 g mandorle pelate/sgusciate

Macro(senza top):
C-49.4 g,P-38 g,G-10 g;kcl 465.
Macro(con top)
C-51.2 g,P-44.8 g,G-26.45 g;kcl 654

Ce ziceti de un chec cu crema de fistic, cu afine si picatele de ciocolata? Pregatiti-va pentru cea mai simpla si mai faina reteta de chec. E gata in 40 de minute cu tot cu timpul de coacere. 😉
Save/comment/❤️

Ingrediente
2 oua
2 lingurite zdravene de miere de albine
40 ml ulei neutru
200 g pasta de fistic indulcita
80 ml lapte
160 g faina de prajituri
1 praf de sare
4 g praf de copt
40 g picatele de ciocolata
40 g afine

Intai de toate preincalzim cuptorul la 180 de grade apoi facem aluatul. 

Intr-un vas incapator amestecam toate ingredientele umede pana se omogenizeaza bine apoi adaugam ingredientele uscate cernute. Omogenizam si turnam in tava tapetata cu hartie de copt. Deasupra presaram afinele spalate si uscate bine. 

Se coace la 170 de grade pentru aproximativ 30 de minute. Testul cu scobitoarea e de ajutor. 

Crema de fistic in combinatie cu ciocolata si cu afinele e de vis. Nu ratati reteta asta ca nu exista una mai simpla. In loc de pasta de fistic se poate folosi inclusiv unt de arahide indulcit.

Aloo Pyaz Ki Sabzi | Potato Onion Curry | 

Music :- Mere Bina ( Lofi Mix ) 

Recipe Instructions 

Heat 1 Big Spoon Oil in a Kadhai 
1/4th Tsp Mustard Seeds 
1/2 Tsp Cumin Seeds 
Pinch Asafoetida 
Sauté Gently 
Add 3 Onions, roughly chopped 
Add 4 Potatoes, chopped 
Salt to Taste 
1 Big Tomato 
1/2 Tsp Turmeric Powder 
1 Tsp Red Chilli Powder 
1 Tsp Coriander Powder 
Pour 1/4th Cup Water 
Close the Lid 
Let it cook for 8-10 Mins 
Keep Checking in intervals 
Add more water if required 
Mix it 2-3 times & let it cook 
Post 10 mins open the Lid & check 
Use a knife to see if potatoes are cooked 
Turn off the gas 
Garnish with Coriander Leaves 
Remove in a serving bowl 
Garnish with Coriander Leaves 
Your Aloo Pyaz Ki Sabzi is ready

Während ich nun meinen Sohn zum ungefähr 16.mal ,(wenn ich mich in dem 16 Jahren nicht verzählt habe)im OP abgegeben habe und nun auf ihn warte, präsentiere ich euch einfach mal ne Runde Wraps. Man muss sich ja irgendwie ablenken. 

Gefüllt mlt Käse,  Hähnchen,  Rucola,  Aioli, Mais und Paprika. Wenn man die Wraps in der Pfanne erhitzt werden sie aussen so schön knusprig und man kann sie besser rollen 😋

Dann warten wir mal weiter......ich hasse es.😒 Zun Glück sind die in unserer Stammklinik alle mega nett. Sie kümmern sich immer toll um seine besonderen Bedürfnisse , wir haben immer ein Zimmer für uns allein und sobald er fertig ist darf ich direkt zu ihm in den Aufwachraum. SALTED CARAMEL CRUNCH SLICE🍫​​​​​​​​
​​​​​​​​
BASE ​​​​​​​​
1 & 2/3 cups almond meal​​​​​​​​
2/3 cup desiccated coconut​​​​​​​​
2 heaped tbsp coconut oil​​​​​​​​
2 tbsp pure maple syrup​​​​​​​​
​​​​​​​​
CARAMEL​​​​​​​​
250g cashew butter​​​​​​​​
1 cup pure maple syrup​​​​​​​​
1 tsp vanilla​​​​​​​​
Salt flakes, to taste​​​​​​​​
​​​​​​​​
TOPPING​​​​​​​​
1 cup roasted skinned hazelnuts OR mixed nuts250g 70-80% organic dark chocolate OR homemade Naked chocolate, melted. ​​​​​​​​
​​​​​​​​
METHOD​​​​​​​​
1. Process all base ingredients until well combined and sticks together. Line a square container with baking paper. Press base in firmly, set aside in the freezer.​​​​​​​​
2. Blend all caramel ingredients together until smooth. Spread over base. Scatter nuts over the slice and press into the caramel gently.​​​​​​​​
3. Pour over melted chocolate. Set in the freezer.​​​​​​​​

Broccoli and cheddar soup using 
@angel.foodnz dairy free smoked cheddar 🧀 🥦

My first time cooking with the smoked cheddar that @angel.foodnz brought out and damn it was good!

What you’ll need:
2 broccoli
2 carrots 
2 celery sticks
2 cloves of garlic 
1 onion
1/4 cup flour
3-4 cups of vegetable stock
2 cups of dairy free milk
3/4 cup coconut cream
1 cup of @angel.foodnz cheddar 

Method:
1. Fry the vegetables until the onion turns translucent. Then sprinkle flour over the veggies and leave cook for a couple more minutes

2. Gradually add the stock and milk whilst stirring consistently to prevent lumps. Then add coconut milk and cheese (you can add more cheese if you want a more cheesy taste or nutritional yeast). Simmer and cook for 15 mins.

3. Add to blender and blend until at desired thickness. Transfer into a bowl with some bread and butter to serve, sprinkle with cheddar on top and enjoy 🥦🌱

INGREDIENTS

For the Soup

2 tbsp olive oil

1 small onion, diced

2 garlic cloves, minced

4 cups chicken broth

1 cup heavy whipping cream

14 oz frozen broccoli floret

3 cups cheddar cheese, shredded

1 oz cream cheese, softened

1/2 tsp kosher salt

1/2 tsp black pepper

1/2 tsp xanthan Gum, optional thickener

For the Garnish

2 pieces of bacon, crumbled

1/2 cup cheddar cheese, shredded

INSTRUCTIONS

Instructions

In a large pot over medium heat, add olive oil, onions, and garlic. Season with salt and pepper. Saute until onions and garlic translucent and tender.

Add chicken broth and heavy cream. Stir, then bring to a simmer.

Add broccoli and cook for 10 minutes, until the broccoli is tender.

Reduce heat to low, and add the cream cheese. Add the shredded cheese one cup at a time, stirring until the cheese is melted and the soup is smooth.

Optional: to thicken the soup, add 1/2 tsp of xanthan gum. Stir well.

Taste for seasoning, and add salt and pepper to taste.

Remove from heat.

PIÑA WHATTHELLADA

Cheesy corn dip

Nici nu are sens sa va explic cat de bun poate fi acest sos de branza si porumb (inspirat de la @halfbakedharvest ). Un sos cremos de cheddar combinat cu boabe de porumb dulci si crocante se prelinge incet si fin pe o bucata crocanta de chips din lipie cu parmezan…take my money! Salvati-va reteta pt urmatorul movie night, beer night, date night sau ati inteles voi, any kinda’ night. O sa va placa. 

Ingrediente:
- 300 g boabe de porumb fiert (poate fi din conserva, congelat si fiert, sau taiat direct de pe știulete)
- 1 ceapa mica spre medie taiata marunt
- 1 ardei gras verde taiat marunt (sau galben, dar nu rosu)
- 200g crema de branza 
- 100-150g smanatana dulce (depinde de consistenta ei, cat e de lichida)
- 100 g cheddar rosu razuit (se gaseste in Mega, Lidl, Auchan, Carrefour, etc)
- Condimente: 1 lgt rasa de pudra de usturoi, 2 lgt boia afumata, sare si piper dupa gust
- Servire: coriandru proaspat sau patrunjel, fulgi de chilli, jalapeño proaspat sau murat, lipie sau tortilla chips

Cum procedati?
✔️Caliti ceapa pt cateva minute apoi ardeiul gras. Nu le caliti prea tare, sa nu fie prea moi. 
✔️Adaugati boabele de porumb fierte si mai lasati pe foc cateva minute amestecand. 
✔️Urmeaza sa puneti peste legume crema de branza si smantana. Amestecati si gatiti pana se omogenizeaza si totul devine cremos.
✔️La final adaugati si condimentele si branza cheddar. Amestecati pe foc pana branza e complet topita si cremoasa. 
✔️Turnati continutul intr-un bol si deasupra coriandrul/patrunjelul proaspat, fulgii de chilli si rondele de jalapeño.
‼️Se serveste obligatiu cald, imediat ce e gata. Pregatiti intai chipsurile apoi dip-ul.

📌Eu am pregatit pe langa acest dip niste chipsuri din lipii. Am uns 3 lipii cu ulei de masline si am presarat deasupra pudra de usturoi. Am taiat lipiile in chipsuri triunghiulare (relativ 🤔 practic doar le-am ciopartit cum am apucat). Le-am asezat in tava, am presarar parmezan ras peste ele si le-am copt pt cateva minute la 180 grade. Dar paziti cuptorul sa nu se arda. Doar cateva minute. 
Swipe pana la final pt un pont.

Instructions

Preheat your oven to 375 degrees f. and line a baking tray with parchment paper.

Lay out the zucchini strips on a large cutting board, lightly sprinkle with sea salt and pepper and very lightly brush with 1 Tablespoon of oil.

Bake strips in your preheated oven for 10-12 minutes, or until slightly tender and easy to roll. Allow them to cool until ready to handle.

Meanwhile, add remaining olive oil in a skillet over medium-high heat. Add minced garlic and cook for 1 minute, until fragrant.

Add in the onions, mushrooms, Italian seasonings and cook for 4-5 minutes.

Stir in 3/4 of the marinara sauce and simmer your mushroom sauce for about 4 minutes, or until slightly reduced.

PARMESAN & GARLIC FRIES 

These were next level, absolutely unreal.. bursting with flavour, and so easy to make. 

First off follow the below recipe for the perfect chips. 

When your chips are cooked pop them aside and get a large high sided pan and drop in a good size knob of butter, you want it to melt and cover the base of the pan. 

Crush 3 garlic cloves and drop into the butter as it starts to melt. Keep on a medium heat for a minute or two and then drop your cooked chips in then pan along with a good shake of grated parmesan.. stir / shake and get them all coated. 

Shake over some dill and a little salt and pepper to serve. 🔥 

Perfect Airfryer Chips

*Don’t worry, if you haven’t got an airfryer you can use the oven (same temp 180). 

Serves 4
1kg potatoes
Low-calorie spray oil
 
1 - Wash and peel your spuds and cut into chips. I like mine chunky but do them the way you like, whether it’s wedges or skinnier French fries.

2 - Pop them in a microwave-safe bowl and give them a good rinse under the tap, then drain ALL the water off; this is very important.

3 - Pop them in the microwave and cook on full power for 12–13 minutes (less if making a smaller batch), giving them a good shake halfway through. You want them to be soft to the touch, but not mushy. Don’t worry if they stick, this is just the starch; you can rinse them again in cold water after microwaving and this will unstick them.

4 - At this point you can season with paprika or garlic granules, but I like mine plain and simple.

5 - Next pop them into the airfryer at 200°C. It will take roughly 15–20 minutes to get them nice and golden, but pay attention to our special trick.

6 - Every 5 minutes I open the basket and give the chips a little spray with my oil and a good shake. This ensures they all cook evenly and end up super crispy from the oil. If I’m cooking for a gang and I have to make a few batches, I leave the made ones in a bowl and just as my last batch is ready I throw them all back in together to heat them up.

This week we are continuing on with another delicious and also healthy Mexican meal plan with our Chicken Tacos, Pico de Gallo and a crunchy and colourful Mexican Bean Salad.⁠
⁠
Click the link in our bio @granluchito or see below for recipe.⁠
⁠
Ingredients - ⁠
Chicken:⁠
500g /1.1 lbs of chicken breasts⁠
2 teaspoons Gran Luchito Smoky Chipotle Fajita and Taco Mix⁠
1 lime (juice)⁠
2 tablespoons olive oil⁠
Salt and freshly ground black pepper (for seasoning)⁠
⁠
Guacamole:⁠
2 ripe avocados⁠
½ red onion (finely diced)⁠
1 jalapeño (finely chopped)⁠
1 tablespoon extra virgin olive oil⁠
⁠
Pico de Gallo:⁠
2 vine tomatoes (diced)⁠
½ red onion (finely diced)⁠
1 tablespoon extra virgin olive oil⁠
1 lime (juice)⁠
1 handful of coriander (roughly chopped)⁠
⁠
To Serve:⁠
6 Gran Luchito Soft Tacos Wraps⁠
⁠
How to make it - ⁠
1. Add the Smoky Chipotle Fajita and Taco Mix onto your chicken breasts with the lime juice, 1 tablespoon of olive oil, a pinch of salt and freshly ground black pepper. Cover with cling film and let it marinate for 20 mins at least.⁠
2. In the meantime prepare a quick guacamole. Add the avocado flesh into a bowl and mash it with a fork. Add the onion, jalapeno, extra virgin olive oil, a pinch of salt and black pepper, then mix and set aside.⁠
3. In a different bowl prepare a quick pico de gallo. Mix the tomatoes, onion, extra virgin olive oil, lime juice, coriander, salt and pepper.⁠
4. Get the barbecue going or heat up a cast-iron skillet with the remaining olive oil. Grill or pan-fry your marinated chicken and let it get a bit of colour on both sides. Finish cooking it covered with a lid, to allow it to cook fully without getting dry.⁠
5. Once ready, remove from the heat and cut the chicken into strips with a sharp knife. Serve your chicken with warm Soft Taco Wraps, a good amount of guacamole and some of the pico de gallo. Finally don’t forget to try some Gran Luchito Salsas!

[Tartelettes Abricots Nectarines et Amandes]
.
Hello hello,
S’il y’a bien un combo qui assure toujours autant de gourmandises eh bien c’est l’amande, en tarte ou gâteau c’est toujours un régal vous n’êtes pas d’accord ? 

Du croquant fondant et de l’acidité, un mariage de 3 saveurs qui combinent parfaitement bien cette tarte de saison.

Pour la recette ⬇️
Ingrédients pour la pâte sucrée:
-200g de farine, -90g de beurre, -50g de sucre, -1oeuf une pincée de sel, 20g d’amandes.
Vous trouverez la recette détaillée sur mes poste à tarte. Après repos étalez la pâte entre deux papiers cuisson et foncez un moule à tartelette beurré ensuite retirez l’excédent, piquez le fond puis réservez 30min au frais le temps de préparer la crème.

Crème d’amandes:
-65g de beurre mou, -65g de sucre, -65g de poudres d’amandes, 1oeuf, 1/2 gousses vanille . 300g d’abricot et 300g de nectarine.
Fouettez le beurre et le sucre, rajoutez l’œuf la vanille puis la poudre d’amandes bien mélangez le tout. Réservez la crème dans une poche à douille et pochez la sur le fond de tarte. Lavez et découpez les fruits en 2 puis en 4 retirez le noyau et disposez les généreusement sur la crème. Enfournez à 180*C pdt 45 à 50min. Laissez refroidir et décorer de fruits frais et compotée. Servir frais !

🌺 *LEMON BUTTER KEBAABS*
🌺

"Rec & pic cred: @mama_taught_me_well
Ruhana Ebrahim

Picture credit : @cook.with.sumz 

INGREDIENTS
Kebabs-
½ kg mutton mince (washed and drained)
1 onion (grated, liquid squeezed out)
2 slices bread (freshly ground)
1 teaspoon salt
½ teaspoon white pepper
1 teaspoon dhana Jeeru (Cumin) (coriander cumin) powder
1 tablespoon ground garlic paste
1 teaspoon ground green chillies
¼ bunch fresh coriander (chopped)

Sauce-
60g butter/rama margarine
1 tablespoon ground garlic paste
½ teaspoon dried mixed herbs
Pinch dhana Jeeru (Cumin) powder
1 teaspoon Aromat (a South African Spice) spice
2 tablespoon flour
1 cup fresh cream
3-4 tablespoon lemon juice

METHOD
Kebabs-
1. Mix everything together.
2. Form round balls with greased hands, the size of a golf ball.
3. Place in the fridge to firm up.
4. Heat a little oil in pot, place kebabs in and cook till browned all over and cooked through.
5. Leave aside.

Sauce-
1. Melt butter in a frying pan.
2. Add flour and whisk to form a smooth roux.
3. Add garlic and braiss for a few seconds.
4. Add in spices and lemon juice, whisk in.
5. Pour in cream and whisk till smooth.
6. Bring sauce to a gentle boil and simmer till sauce thickens.
7. Switch off heat.
8. With a slotted spoon, remove kebabs from pot and place into sauce.
9. Allow to heat together.
10. Do not overcook sauce as it may split.
#mamataughtmewellrecipes

INFO & TIPS
Note: can replace with chicken or beef mince"

There was a trend for spiralised vegetables a while ago. They're great if you're trying to cut out carbs like pasta or are gluten free and need an alternative. Spirals also give salads a new and interesting look & might just tempt fussy kids to try something different.
The best veg for spiraling is anything with a firm flesh, so squash, courgette, beetroot, carrots, parsnips, turnip, potatoes, cucumber & celeriac are all good choices.
Apples & pears will also spiral. There are a wide range of spiralisers out there to suit most bugets, here's a link to my blog with a 3 different recipes to try https://buff.ly/2SlioaI

⁣Caprese Chicken with Pesto 🌿🍅⠀
⠀
This dish is a perfect light dinner for the warm weather we’ve been having and so easy to cook with hardly any ingredients needed! ⠀
⠀
Ingredients:⠀
🍅1 chicken breast⠀
🍅1 ball mozarella cheese ⠀
🍅2 tomatoes ⠀
🍅small handful of basil ⠀
🍅pesto ⠀
🍅balsamic glaze ⠀
⠀
For the chicken: ⠀
preheat the oven to 180 degrees ⠀
Chop your tomatoes ans mozarella into even slices ⠀
Cut slices into the chicken breast deep enough for the stuffing ⠀
Place the chicken breast on the oven tray and place slices of mozarella and tomato into the slices made in the chicken ⠀
Top with 2 teaspoons of pesto, salt & pepper⠀
Cook in the oven for roughly 30 mins till the chicken is cooked through ⠀
Top with fresh basil & serve ⠀
⠀
For the caprese salad:⠀
Lay out even slices of tomato and mozarella on your plate ⠀
Lightly drizzle olive oil & balsamic glaze⠀
Top with salt, pepper & fresh basil ⠀
⠀
Enjoy! ⠀
⠀
This was delicious and minimum effort so is perfect for a weekday meal 😋⠀

👶 Baby Friendly👶

Ingrediente:

☆100g unt cu 65% grăsime @lidlromania
☆30g smântână cu 30% grasime @lidlromania
☆100g făină albă tip 650

☆1 ou
☆1 linguriță praf de copt bio @biomarketro

☆gem de prune fără zahăr @niavis.ro 
☆brânză de vaci @lidlromania 
☆mascarpone @lidlromania 
☆zmeură @piataobor.bucuresti

Mod de preparare:

☆Se lasă untul la temperatura camereu ca să se înmoaie și apoi îl mixăm impreună cu smântâna, siropul de cocos și oul
☆Adăugăm apoi, făina, praful de copt, vanilia și mai mixăm puțin
☆Frământăm puțin aluatul cu mâna și apoi îl punem în folie alimentară și îl lăsăm la frigider în jur de 30 de minute
☆Scoatem aluatul, îl împărțim în mai multe bucăți și începem să întindem cu ajutorul unui făcăleț fiecare bucată
☆Tăiem aluatul în trigunghiuri și umplem cu gem sau cremă de brânză, mascarpone și zmeură (le amestecăm înainte pe cele 3 ingrediente pentru a obține o cremă)
☆Când am format toate cornulețele, le punem într-o tavă pe folie de copt și le dăm la cuptor, la 180 de grade, până când se rumenesc deasupra

1.Stavite jednu Rawbite pločicu u blender ili u multipraktik i miksajte dok ne dobijete mrvičastu smjesu. Stavite smjesu u zdjelu.
2. Zajedno s ostalim sastojcima stavite drugu RAWBITE pločicu u blender i ponovno izmiksajte. Smoothie treba biti dovoljno tekuć da se može preliti. Ako nije dovoljno tekuće, dodajte još kokosove vode.
3. Ulijte smoothie u 4 kalupa za sladoled i pospite ih mrvicama od prve Rawbite pločice.
4. Zamrznite najmanje 4 sata prije uživanja u proteinskim sladoledima RAWBITE!

Uživajte u svakom zalogaju! 🥰

CURRIED VEGGIE NOODLES 🍜 🌱 another high protein vegan meal ~ takes about 10 minutes to whip up + is super filling. And delicious of course!!
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
Weekday lunches/dinners at their very finest 🤌🏼
✅Over 30g protein per serve too!
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
I know the cauliflower chips on top is super random but I had them in the cupboard and I love some crunch on a stir fry, so this worked perfectly!!😆🤗
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
RECIPE (makes 2 serves):
100-150g @nooeynoods lupin fettuccine, or edamame noodles
1 carrot, diced 
1/2 onion, diced
1 cup broccoli, diced 
2 cloves of garlic, thinly sliced 
1 cup kale, chopped 
3 mushrooms, sliced 
2 tsp curry paste
1 tsp curry powder 
1 tbsp soy sauce or tamari 
2 tbsp sweet chilli sauce
Juice 1/2 lemon
Handful of curry cauliflower chips, to serve 
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
1️⃣Heat a pan with a lil sesame oil, then stir fry carrot, broccoli, onion, garlic + mushroom until just soft.
2️⃣Cook noodles according to packet directions.
3️⃣Add curry paste, curry powder, soy sauce, sweet chilli, lemon, kale and noodles to pan. Keep cooking until kale is wilted.
4️⃣Serve topped cauliflower chips!
ENJOY 💛💛

🍅 QUICHE D’ETE 🧀 

La Covid est repassée par là mais la faim est toujours là 😆 donc on cuisine !

Pour la pâte :
🌼 220g de farine (ici, 70g de farine complète + 150g de farine de blé)
🌼 30g d’huile de Colza
🌼 environ 100ml d’eau

Pour l’appareil :
🌼 4 oeufs
🌼 20cl de crème fraîche 15% MG
🌼 1 tomate 
🌼 200g de Comté râpé
🌼 100g d’emmental râpé 
🌼 Poivre,Thym frais, et basilic

1- Fais ta pâte feuilletée en mélangeant tous les ingrédients. Forme une boule puis étale ta pâte. 
2- Fais des trous sur le fond de ta pâte à l’aide d’une fourchette.
3- Mélange tous les ingrédients de l’appareil sauf la tomate. 
4- Verse l’appareil dans le fond de tarte puis ajoute la tomate découpée en rondelles. 
5- Referme les bords façon tarte rustique. 
6- Enfourne dans un four préchauffé à 180 degrés pendant environ 35 min. 

Servir tiède ou froid 🤤

Aloo Pyaz Ki Sabzi | Potato Onion Curry | 

Music :- Mere Bina ( Lofi Mix ) 

Recipe Instructions 

Heat 1 Big Spoon Oil in a Kadhai 
1/4th Tsp Mustard Seeds 
1/2 Tsp Cumin Seeds 
Pinch Asafoetida 
Sauté Gently 
Add 3 Onions, roughly chopped 
Add 4 Potatoes, chopped 
Salt to Taste 
1 Big Tomato 
1/2 Tsp Turmeric Powder 
1 Tsp Red Chilli Powder 
1 Tsp Coriander Powder 
Pour 1/4th Cup Water 
Close the Lid 
Let it cook for 8-10 Mins 
Keep Checking in intervals 
Add more water if required 
Mix it 2-3 times & let it cook 
Post 10 mins open the Lid & check 
Use a knife to see if potatoes are cooked 
Turn off the gas 
Garnish with Coriander Leaves 
Remove in a serving bowl 
Garnish with Coriander Leaves 
Your Aloo Pyaz Ki Sabzi is ready

Perfekt als leckerer Energieschub am Morgen oder für zwischendurch.
Ich hab mir heut den leckeren Bananen-Kaffee-Smoothie als Energiekick für zwischendurch auf Arbeit gemacht.

Durch die Banane und den Kakao stillt er perfekt die Lust auf Süßes und der Kaffee liefert die Energie.
Der Bananen-Kaffee-Smoothie hat nur winzige 122kcal und passt somit immer rein 🤗

Die Zutaten für 2 Portionen findet ihr wenn ihr nach rechts swiped ➡️
Die Zubereitung ist wieder ganz schnell und einfach 😊:
Zuerst die Haferflocken mit dem Mixer(ich mach alles mit dem Smoothiemaker) zu Mehl mahlen, dann Kakao und Zimt dazu geben und noch eine Runde drehen lassen, dass sich die trockenen Zutaten miteinander vermischen.
Dann die restlichen Zutaten hinzugeben (Kaffee kalt) und im Smoothiemaker mixen.

Entweder sofort genießen oder bis zum Genuss kühl stellen 😊

[RECIPE]

SALTED CARAMEL CRUNCH SLICE🍫​​​​​​​​
​​​​​​​​
BASE ​​​​​​​​
1 & 2/3 cups almond meal​​​​​​​​
2/3 cup desiccated coconut​​​​​​​​
2 heaped tbsp coconut oil​​​​​​​​
2 tbsp pure maple syrup​​​​​​​​
​​​​​​​​
CARAMEL​​​​​​​​
250g cashew butter​​​​​​​​
1 cup pure maple syrup​​​​​​​​
1 tsp vanilla​​​​​​​​
Salt flakes, to taste​​​​​​​​
​​​​​​​​
TOPPING​​​​​​​​
1 cup roasted skinned hazelnuts OR mixed nuts250g 70-80% organic dark chocolate OR homemade Naked chocolate, melted. ​​​​​​​​
​​​​​​​​
METHOD​​​​​​​​
1. Process all base ingredients until well combined and sticks together. Line a square container with baking paper. Press base in firmly, set aside in the freezer.​​​​​​​​
2. Blend all caramel ingredients together until smooth. Spread over base. Scatter nuts over the slice and press into the caramel gently.​​​​​​​​
3. Pour over melted chocolate. Set in the freezer.​​​​​​​​
​​​​​​​​
Slice and enjoy!

Looking for a fast recipe to make for lunch? This dish is light and can be made in only 25 minutes!

✨Bok Choy with Tamari Sauce✨

Ingredients:
✅2 lb bok choy, small 
✅1 Tbs ginger, fresh, minced
✅ 1/4 cup scallions, thinly sliced 
✅1 1/2 Tbs olive oil, divided ✅6 Tbs tamari sauce 
✅1 Tbs hemp seeds 

Directions:
Prep : 
1. Trim bok choy bottoms and cut in half lengthwise. 
2. Mince ginger. 
3. Slice scallions. 

Make :
1. Coat bottom of pan with 1 1/2 teaspoons oil, over medium-high heat. When hot, lay bok choy in single layer, cut side down (do not overcrowd). Add 2 tablespoons water and cover about 2 minutes. 

2. Lift out of pan, drain, and place on platter. Remove water from pan and repeat with remaining bok choy. Leave residual water in pan. 

3. Add 1 tablespoon oil and ginger to pan and cook, stirring over high 
heat until ginger is browned. Remove from heat and add tamari sauce. 

4. Pour sauce over bok choy, sprinkle with scallions and hemp seeds.

Bonjour à tous ! 🥰

Nous savons tous que l’été, l’apéro coule à flot, donc voici une nouvelle petite recette pour accompagner vos belles soirées. 🌞

Ingrédients :

- 20g de son d’avoine
- 50g de mélange de graines (courge, tournesol, sésame…)
- 65g de farine d’épeautre 
- Thym
- Sel, poivre 🧂
- 25g d’huile 
- 65g d’eau

Étapes :

- Préchauffez votre four à 180°C. 
- Mélangez tous les ingrédients secs ensemble.
- Ajoutez l'eau et l'huile puis mélangez avec une spatule.
- Étalez la pâte en couche fine sur une feuille de papier sulfurisé.
- Enfournez délicatement la pâte finement étalée dans le four pour 25 min (ou davantage selon le four)
- Sortez la plaque, laissez refroidir puis cassez des petites morceaux avec les mains.

Optionnel : Parsemez la pâte de fromage râpé avant d’enfourner.

Sweet & Savoury Mushroom Scones~🍄 This easy and quick snack made with our favourite mushrooms is definitely a pleaser. We love having them with cream cheese, random toppings and even on its own.😋 Mama also made them petite so it's easy to pack them along as mini treats for the kids' outings! ❤
.
Ingredients:
200g swiss brown mushrooms, chopped 
220g all purpose flour
20g sugar
6g baking powder
½ tsp salt
1 tsp #lilomushroompowder
55g cold butter, cut into small cubes
25g beaten egg
Approx. 100ml milk 
.
Method:
✔In a pan, sauté chopped mushrooms with some butter till slightly brown and set aside to cool
✔Combine flour, sugar, baking powder, salt and #lilomushroompowder in a bowl
✔Rub in butter cubes with fingers until the mixture resembles breadcrumbs before adding in the sautéed mushrooms 
✔Add in beaten egg and milk, and mix with a spatula until just combined with no dry flour remaining (add more milk if required)
✔Turn the dough out onto a floured surface and sprinkle some flour on top
✔Pat the dough down lightly to about 3cm thick and cut straight down with a round cutter without twisting it
✔Gather the loose pieces of dough into a ball and pat down again to cut out more
✔Brush the top of the scones with egg and bake in a preheated oven for 15-20 minutes at 180°C till golden brown
.

Lamb Kebabs With Fresh Mint And Pomegranate 
Cooking in the summer is ridiculously easy. A little bit of prep work in the morning, let the flavours come together while your meat and veggies marinate all day, fire up the grill that night, and within 20 minutes, your gourmet meal is ready.

Lamb is one of my favourite meats because it is tender and juicy, especially when cooked to medium-rare. While I am a massive fan of a rack of lamb, this was my first attempt at cooking a leg of lamb. I have grown accustomed to ordering lamb kebabs when I'm out to dinner because I'm not sure I'm patient enough for the long slow roasting process.

This lamb kebab recipe was perfect because (aside from the 30 minutes it took to break it down- it was my first time, don't judge!), the rest was super quick and easy. The pomegranate molasses bring a tart tang that complements the lamb's earthy flavour, and the fresh mint helps balance out the sweetness.

Cukety se sýrem

Cuketa je moje velmi oblíbená surovina. Dá se jíst na mnoho způsobů a nikdy nezklame. Když není čas, sáhnu po této velmi rychlé, ale velmi chutné variantě. Ani se nezdá, ale docela zasytí. Ideální na letní večeři

Suroviny na cca 2 porce:
1 ks střední cukety
1 ks mozzarelly
100 g nivy
2 PL olivového oleje
1 stroužek česneku
Hrstka bylinek (oregano, tymián, co máte rádi)

Postup:
1. Cuketu omyjeme a nakrájíme na kolečka
2. Česnek utřeme a smícháme s olejem a bylinkami
3. Potřeme cuketu směsí
4. Mozzarellu nakrájíme na kolečka a dáme na cuketu
5. Nivu nastrouháme a nasypeme na mozzarellu
6. Pečeme na 170 stupňů, cca 15 minut (ideálně posledních 5 minut pustit gril shora)
Pozn.: cuketu nesolíme, aby nepustila hodně tekutiny. A niva je taktéž slaná dost

Buongiorno!💙
Manca sempre meno alla mia partenza per le vacanze, quindi si prospettano dei giorni impegnativi e da organizzare al meglio per poter fare tutto..lavoro, allenamenti, casa e commissioni. Questa mattina post camminata mattutina colazione veloce e buonissima con Piada-Cake alla VANIGLIA con MIRTILLI 🫐 e CREMA DI MANDORLE TOSTATE.
La piada 🥞è sempre una soluzione pratica, sana e gustosa anche per chi ha poco tempo.
Ecco la ricetta.👇🏻
Ingredienti:
-130 gr di albume 
- 60 gr di farina di avena alla vaniglia 
- 10 gr di farina di cocco 
-100 gr di mirtilli 
-5 gr di bicarbonato 
-10 gr di succo di limone
-15 gr crema di mandorle tostate 

Procedimento:
Unire le farine, l’albume e acqua quanto basta e mescolare. Aggiungere il bicarbonato e il succo di limone e mescolare nuovamente finché il composto non sarà omogeneo. Nel frattempo scaldare un pentolino da 20 cm. Versare il composto nel pentolino e cuocere per circa 20 minuti con coperchio. Una volta cotto adagiare la piada su un piatto e finire con i mirtilli e la crema di mandorle tostate.

Gustare! 😘

VEGAN BBQ IDEEËN 🌽💯

Bbq'en zonder vlees?! Vijf jaar geleden had ik je raar aangekeken 🤨, maar met de huidige kennis en ook het aanbod in de supermarkten is er geen reden meer om te kiezen voor vlees (waar een dier voor dood is gegaan).. 🤷‍♀️ Als je dezelfde ervaring wilt als een stuk vlees dan is er voor elk soort een plantaardige & diervriendelijkere versie 🌱. De smaak, de textuur en de ervaring is hetzelfde al dan niet beter!! (er gaat geen onschuldig beest voor dood)

Dat het duurder is 🤑, kan nu ook niet meer als argument gebruikt worden tegen plantaardige vleesopvolgers, want @proveg.nl kwam recentelijk met een onderzoek waaruit geconcludeerd is dat plantaardige vleesopvolgers goedkoper zijn dan hun dier onvriendelijke tegenhangers 🥳. 

Dit is natuurlijk meer dan geweldig nieuws!! Ik hoop dat we ooit mogen zeggen "ooit aten we vlees". Dat zou toch geweldig zijn voor de aarde, de arme/ondervoede mensen en alle dieren 🌿🐖🐮🐤.

Ik wilde eigenlijk alleen wat ideeën voor een vegan bbq met jullie delen maar toen kwam dit hele, hopelijk inspiratievolle verhaal op papier 😊.

1️⃣ Spiesjes met gemarineerde tofu, rode en gele paprika & rode ui.
2️⃣ Maiskolven besmeerd met een sausje van olijfolie, maple syrup, knoflookpoeder en paprikapoeder.
3️⃣ Mashed aardappelen met een sausje van oa olijfolie, maple syrup en zes teentjes knoflook 🧄😋.

Inspireer elkaar 🤍. Samen staan we sterk!

Oats Pongal with Ghee and Black pepper.

RECIPE:
Mix ½ Cup easy to cook oats with 1 Cup water. Cook on low flame while stirring. Add a little bit of salt, grated ginger, curry leaves, crushed black pepper. Paneer Tikka Recipe😍
Save it to try later♥️

Ingredients :-

Curd - 1/2 Cup
Roasted Gram Flour - 1.5tbsp
Carom Seeds/Ajwain - 1/4tsp
Ginger  Garlic Paste - 1tbsp
Kashmiri Red Mirch - 1tbsp
Cumin Powder - 1/2tsp
Black Pepper Powder - 1/2tsp
Turmeric Powder - 1/2tsp
Salt as per taste
Chaat Masala - 1tsp
Garam Masala - 1tsp
Lemon Juice - 1tsp
Kasuri Methi
Hot Mustard Oil - 1.5tbsp
Diced Paneer - 200gms
Diced Capsicum + Onion + Tomato(1 each)

Mix everything well and marinate for 20 mins.
📌Arrange in Skewers one by one.
Apply Butter/Oil in a pan and shallow fry it for 5 mins from all sides(medium flame).

Tip :- Soak Skewers in water for 10 mins before use.

Колачи со овес и со путер од кикирики

Енергетски здрави колачи
Без бело брашно и бел шеќер

Потребно е
✅1 јајце
✅2 чаши ситен овес
✅1/2 чаша путер од кикирики
✅1/2чаша мед
✅1 1/2 м.л пециво
✅1/2 м.л сода бикарбона
✅1 м.л цимет
✅ 1/2 чаша чоколадни топчиња

Подготовка
Измешајте ги сувите состојки во еден сад.
Во друг сад ставете јајце, путер од кикирики, мед и на крај се убаво измешајте. Додадете ги чоколадните топчиња и покријте го садот со фолија и ставете да отстои 30 минути во фрижидер. 
Со лажица за сладолед ставете еднаква количина од смесата и обликувајте ги колачите. Може смесата да е леплива, натопете ги рацете со вода. 
Печете во загреана рерна  на 180с околу 10 минути, да добијат златеста боја (зависи од рерната)

𝚂𝚞𝚜𝚑𝚒 𝙱𝚘𝚠𝚕 𝚖𝚒𝚝 𝚖𝚊𝚛𝚒𝚗𝚒𝚎𝚛𝚝𝚎𝚖 𝙻𝚊𝚌𝚑𝚜 ♥︎ 

𝚐𝚕𝚞𝚝𝚎𝚗𝚏𝚛𝚎𝚒 ♡︎ 𝚕𝚊𝚌𝚝𝚘𝚜𝚎𝚏𝚛𝚎𝚒 

Zutaten: ( für 2 Personen) 

* 175g Sushi Reis 
* 30 Reisessig 
* Etwas Zucker ca. 5-10g 
* 225ml Wasser 
* 1 Mango 
* 1/4 Gurke 
* 1 Avocado 
* ca. 100- 150g Edamame (TK) 
* 150-180g Sashimi Lachs (ca. 75g p.P) 
* 1-2 EL Glutenfreie Soja Soße 
* 1-2 TL Majo 
* 1-2 TL Sirachia Soße 

Zubereitung: 
Den Sushi Reis nach Packungsanweisung im besten Fall ein paar Stunden zuvor zubereiten und kaltstellen. Optional lässt sich auch der Sushi Reis gegen normaler Reis oder eine andere Alternative ersetzen. 

Die restlichen Toppings in mundgerechte Stücke würfeln. 
Die Edamame auftauen lassen und ggf. kurz mit warmen Wasser etwas abspülen. 

Den in Stücke geschnittenen Lachs mit etwas glutenfreier Sojasauce, der Majo und Sirachia Soße abschmecken. 

Alles in einer Bowl anrichten. 
Mit Sojasoße und eingelegtem Ingwer servieren. 

Auch ein sehr leckeres Sommeressen. Vor allem wenn der Reis in größeren Mengen zubereitet wird, ist es auch super schnell gemacht. (hierfür einfach die Menge des Reises verdoppeln).

Filipino Chicken Noodle Soup (Sopas). Creamy soup with shredded chicken, hot dogs, and macaroni!!!! 

Ingredients & Recipe
1-2 pieces of boned in chicken breast
3 pieces hot dogs, sliced
6 cups water or broth
1 chicken bouillon
1 small onion
2 cloves of garlic, minced 
2 cups elbow pasta
1 carrot, julienned 
1 celery, sliced
1/2 cup cabbage
2 cup milk
1 tbsp fish sauce
1 tbsp cooking oil
Salt and pepper

1. In a large pot, heat oil under medium high heat. 
2. Sauté onions and garlic for 2-3 minutes. 
3. Add chicken breasts, seasoning with salt and pepper, searing all sides. 
4. Add water, bouillon, and fish sauce. 
5. Under low medium heat, cook chicken for 2 hours. Skimming off scum. 
6. While chicken is cooking heat a small pan and toast macaroni just until it turns light brown. Remove from heat and set aside. 
7. Remove chicken and shred meat, discarding bones and skin. 
8. Place shredded chicken and hot dogs back into pot. 
9. Add celery, carrots, and macaroni cooking for an additional 7 minutes. 
10. Add cabbage and milk, cooking for an additional 5 minutes. 
11. Season with additional salt and pepper as needed. 
12. Serve immediately.

Instagram reels are the key to gaining growth on the platform so its crucial to know how to successfully create one. Here’s how:

1️⃣ Use On-Screen Text and Captions - Adding on-screen text and subtitles to your videos is a no-brainer when it comes to reaching more users. Plus, not only are subtitles great for people who watch without sound, but they’re invaluable for those with hearing difficulties.

2️⃣ Use Trends as Inspiration - Similar to TikTok, Reels come and go quite quickly. To hop on a trend before it becomes old news, take a few minutes each morning to scroll through the Instagram Reels tab and other creators’ profiles to see what they’re sharing. Is there anything that seems to consistently pop up — a particular song? An audio clip? A dance trend? If so, click on the music to see how many other creators have used the audio. Scroll through the videos to get an idea of what the trend is.

3️⃣ Drive Traffic by Encouraging Viewers to Head to Your Link in Bio - The best way to drive traffic from Reels is by including a clear call-to-action (CTA) that encourages people to head to your link in bio. This could be with on-screen text placement, a verbal call-out, in your video caption, or all of the above. You can also use a link in the bio tool to create a mini landing page with multiple link buttons and clickable images.

4️⃣ Find Your Niche and Post Consistently - One of the best ways to gain virality on Instagram Reels is by finding your niche and posting consistently. There are so many Instagram users with a wide range of interests and hobbies. No matter what your brand or business does, there’s a niche for you!

5️⃣ Include 3-5 Hashtags - Including 3-5 hashtags can be a great way to help the Instagram algorithm “understand” your content and serve it to relevant audiences. For example, using hashtags like #easyrecipes, #mealideas and #dinnerinspiration will indicate to the Instagram Reels algorithm that your content is about food — which may increase the likelihood of it being served to users who are actively engaging with similar content.

Shaved Steak & Asiago Sandwich (15 min prep-to-table)
1. Mince fresh garlic. Add olive oil to pan and roast garlic, leaving slightly raw.
2. Add sliced onions to oil and cook until tender. Salt and pepper. Remove from heat.
3. Add shaved flank steak to pan. Season with garlic, cracked black pepper, and salt. Cook to medium rare. Remove from heat. 
4. Butter sourdough bread. Spread pesto on one side, garlic truffle aioli on the other.
5. Begin frying bread on pan. Add shaved parmesan and Asiago cheese to one side.
6. As cheese starts to melt, add steak and onions on one slice of bread. Top with cheese and close slices.
7. Roast both sides of sandwich equally.
8. Serve with side salad with balsamic vinaigrette and enjoy!

Tabbouleh (1 hr prep-to-table)
1. Wash and chop fresh parsley into fine pieces.
2. Dice baby tomatoes into fine pieces.
3. Dice cucumbers into small pieces. 
4. Cut green onions into fine pieces.
5. Slice mint into fine pieces.
6. Add ingredients into a large bowl. Add olive oil and fresh minced garlic.
7. Squeeze half a lemon in. Press and mix with hands, taking care to express the juices. Ideally, let sit for 15 min-overnight.
8. Add couscous, mix, and serve!

Boscaiola! @rumourhasit9 had cooked this for my family and I and It’s now my go too for family meals. It’s a clean pasta that’s not too heavy, not too light and full of goodies.

Ingredients:
8 oz any mushrooms you can find
5-7 slices of prosciutto
1/3 cup sun dried tomato
1/4 cup white wine
2-3 sprigs of thyme
1 cup heavy cream
3 cloves garlic
2 Tbsp parsley
1 Tbsp butter
1/2 cup parmesan
12 oz pasta of choice
Optional: Chili flakes to your liking

-Finely chop your garlic, parsley, sun dried tomato, and thyme. -Thinly slice mushrooms and prosciutto.
-In a sauce pan on medium heat, add some oil and cook mushrooms till brown (5-7 mins). 
-Season with salt and pepper, then add a Tbsp of butter.
-Add the prosciutto. Once heated through add the garlic and chili flakes.
-Toss in the sun dried tomatoes and thyme, then deglaze with white wine.
-Once the white wine has reduced significantly, add the heavy cream and mix. 
-Let the flavors get to know each other then add your cooked pasta, parmesan and parsley.
-Give it a good mix, add some pasta water to thin out the sauce if needed.
-Serve and enjoy! 🍝

INGREDIENTS
1 tablespoon olive oil
1 medium onion (chopped)
4 medium carrots (peeled and cut into 1/4-inch pieces)
4 ribs celery (chopped)
3 cloves garlic (minced)
1 teaspoon dried oregano
½ teaspoon dried thyme
1 bay leaf
¾ teaspoon salt (or to taste)
¼ teaspoon black pepper
4 cups low sodium chicken broth
4 cups water (or chicken broth)
1 pound boneless, skinless chicken breasts
6 ounces egg noodles
chopped fresh parsley (optional, for serving)

INSTRUCTIONS
Press the sauté button on the Instant Pot and add the olive oil to the pot. Once the pot is hot, add the onion, carrots and celery and cook, stirring occasionally, until veggies start to soften, about 3 minutes. Stir in the garlic.
Press "Cancel" to turn off the Instant Pot.
Add the dried oregano, thyme, bay leaf, salt, pepper, broth and water to the pot. Stir. Nestle the chicken into the broth.
Close the Instant Pot lid and turn the valve to the sealing position. Pressure cook on high pressure for 7 minutes. The Instant Pot will take about 20 minutes to reach pressure and then the cook time will begin counting down.

Hi besties! I thought it was time I’d share one of my all time favorite recipes. It’s a deliciously creamy coconut curry that I’ve been making for a couple of years now. It’s the perfect comfort food in my opinion. 

THAI RED COCONUT CURRY CHICKEN
(ft my sous chef @izza.rehman & photographer @sa_herrr)
Ingredients:
* 1 pound thinly sliced chicken thighs 
* 1 jar Maesri red curry paste
* 2 tbsp lemongrass paste plus a teaspoon of fresh minced lemongrass 
* 1-2 diced shallots 
* 2 minced garlic cloves
* About an inch of minced ginger
*2 thinly sliced bell peppers 
* 1 can coconut milk
* 1 can coconut cream 
* 1 tbsp fish sauce (optional)
* a few Kaffir lime leaves 
* 2 tbsp brown sugar 
* 2 minced Thai chilies 
* 1/2 - 1 juiced lime
* 1/4 cup chopped Thai basil
*1/4 cup toasted cashews

-In a large pan, brown your chicken over medium high heat until no longer pink.
-Add your red curry paste along with the fresh lemongrass and lemongrass paste, garlic, ginger and shallot. Mix with the chicken and sauté until aromatic. 
-Add your bell peppers and cook for a couple of more minutes and then bring the heat down to medium and add your coconut milk and cream. Let it simmer for a couple of minutes and then add the kaffir lime leaves, Thai chilies and brown sugar. 
-Stir well and cook for a few more minutes and then take off heat. 
-Add your Thai basil, toasted cashews and lime juice and serve over rice. Enjoy!

Why is canned tuna so cheap when fresh tuna is so expensive? 

Tuna salad:
- Tuna+mayo+salt+yogurt+lime
- Red coral lettuce 
- Baby cos lettuce 
- Butterhead lettuce
- Fresh shallots 
- Goji berries 
- Spring onions 
- Hard boiled egg 

Well it basically comes down to what is described as "sushinomics". Tuna that is canned are species that reproduce quickly creating a vast supply (albacore, yellowtail etc.) But are considered less tasty. The ones that are used for sashimi and sushi are the Bluefin tuna which not only require more efforts in catch but are also low in supply. With the fish only reaching reproductive at 8 years and only having a life span of around 40 years, there aren't much to go around. Overfishing has also greatly contributed to the decline in supply of bluefins as they are being caught before being able to reproduce. Lack in regulation will likely lead to extinction of these tasty swimmers. Luckily there are efforts being put forward and the status of bluefin have been reduce from endangered to least concern. Which is great but it needs to be continued because they taste so good 🥺.

Oh and side note: if you dont want to add alot of mayo to your tuna; sub with unsweetened yogurt, lime and salt. Gives it a fresh taste and adds a 'lil probiotics to you diet.

Air Fryer* Beef Roast 

Let your  unthawed roast get to room temperature. 

Preheat air fryer to 400° until nice and hot, about 10 min. 

Cut off excess fat off roast, pat dry with a paper towel and top with some olive oil (1 TBSP), and rub with onion soup mix (about 2 TBSP)  and a sprinkle of pepper. 

Line the air fryer basket with parchment paper and let the roast cook at 400° for 8 minutes. 

Turn the temperature down to 350°, flip over the roast and cook it for another 25-30 min. 

Let sit for 20 Minutes and Enjoy!

I sliced mine and used for sandwiches with toasted bread, sliced cheese, garlic mayo and sauted onions and mushrooms!!

I highly recommend- my husband said it was the best roast beef sandwich he has ever had.

I M P O R T A N T ⚠️

16 oz fettuccine pasta

Less sodium Montreal steak seasoning
Olive oil
1 stick (8 tbsp) unsalted butter
5 minced garlic cloves
3 tbsp all purpose flour
3 cups heavy cream
1 cup pasta water
1 cup shredded Parmesan cheese( not the one in a bottle)
1 cup white cheesy cheese
1/2 tsp garlic powder
1/2 tsp Italian seasoning
1 tsp black pepper
Salt 
1 serving of love 💕

Cajun Ranchero Pork Chops w/ Asparagus

• 8  boneless thin sliced pork chops
• 1 packet ranch seasoning 
• 1 tsp. Pink Himalayan Salt 🧂 
• 2 tsp. Black Pepper 
• 2 tsp. Paprika
• 2 tsp. Garlic Powder 🧄 
• 1 ziplock bag 
• 1 bag steamable asparagus 

- Combine ingredients & shake well

- Refrigerate overnight 

- Set Air Fryer to 380° for 19 minutes

- Turn over at 11 minutes 

- Turn over at 3 minutes (I added 2 minutes for a total of 5 minutes remaining)

- Steam Asparagus as directed (I use steam in bag 4 minutes)

😋 Have you seen us on TV and wondered how to make the Shakshuka? Here’s an easy Shakshuka recipe by @yvonnemsw that you can try at home with our fiber-rich Ayam Brand Baked Beans for a hearty and delicious meal. ❤️

Baked Beans Shakshuka 

Ingredients
- 1 can Ayam Brand Baked Beans In Tomato Sauce 
- 4 tbsp Ayam Brand Tomato Puree
- 1/2 Yellow Onion, diced
- 1/3 Red Capsicum, diced
- 3 Eggs
- 4 tbsp Mozzarella Cheese
- Salt & Pepper, to taste
- Dried Rosemary 
- Parsley 
- Sourdough, toasted

Method
1. Heat up skillet with olive oil and sauté onion till soften.
2. Add in baked beans, tomato puree and capsicum.
3. Season with salt and rosemary.
4. Crack the eggs in, cover and simmer till eggs almost cook.
5. Add mozzarella and black pepper and cook till cheese is melted. 
6. Garnish with parsley and serve with toasted buttered sourdough!

Feeling the Burnout? Here’s how to get over it! 🌼

We are halfway through the year – do you feel like you are losing motivation, struggling to get out of bed, the tiredness is visible on your face, or you just CANNOT wrap your head around life, concepts & daily things? 
feeling burnout can lead to many emotional and physical challenges!

I have been finding myself slip into that phase – not healthy – but the best part is that the moment we recognize – its easy to snap out of it and start practicing these small habits. 
 
✨Set aside time for yourself: everyday a minimum of 1 hour without emails and work doing an activity that you enjoy (ex: photography, painting, reading) – for me I love journaling, editing & sharing experiences.

✨Analyze your current situation – are you able to rest well? 

✨ Get outdoors if you can – nature does wonders 

✨Get sleep – if your regular hours are 7 – bump it up to 2 more hours – if you can (if possible on weekend – refrain from setting an alarm) 

✨The right diet – flourish that gut with all the right nutrients – research shows (gut brain connection is real) 

Sending you all loveeee and positivity this lovely Monday 💗💗

W E E T B I X  S L I C E

So here's my version of Weetbix Slice for all those folks who messaged me for the recipe after seeing my stories...not many slices left to take a good photo, as it doesn't last long in our house.

BASE

In a bowl...
4 Weetbix - crushed
1 1/3 cup All purpose flour (plain) 
3/4 cup sugar (I like to use coconut sugar but white is fine) 
6 teaspoons unsweetened cocoa powder
2 teaspoons baking powder 
1/2 cup desiccated coconut 
100gms dark chocolate - break-up 
200gms butter - melt 
2 teaspoons vanilla extract

GANACHE 

1 1/2 cup icing sugar 
6 teaspoons unsweetened cocoa powder 
Desiccated coconut 
1 teaspoon vanilla extract 
6 teaspoons butter - melted 
Milk 

MAKE

▪︎Line 20x20 baking tin
▪︎In bowl add weetbix, flour, sugar, cocoa, desiccated coconut + baking powder
▪︎Melt dark chocolate + butter on low till blended then and add vanilla extract 
▪︎Pour melted mix into dry ingredients and mix well
▪︎ Pour mix into lined baking tray and press firmly + evenly down
▪︎ Place on middle shelf in pre-warmed med oven and bake for 10-15mins. Don't over cook or your slice will be dry.
▪︎ Cool down in pan and add ganache

MAKE GANACHE

In a bowl, sift icing sugar + cocoa powder then add vanilla extract and melted butter. Begin to mix and slowly add milk till your desired whippiness. Make sure you blend all the lumps out. Spread onto cooled slice and sprinkle with desiccated coconut. Cut slice into desired size and EAT! 

Best kept in airtight container in the fridge.

PS...I like to add nuts into the base or sprinkle chopped up + toasted macadamia nuts on top for crunch. Or you can even add those scrappy bits of cereal or muesli into your base...the options are endless!

TPW X

Garden fresh deconstructed zucchini boat casserole❤️ This was seriously soooo delicious😋 

Preheat oven to 350- Sauté diced onions🧅peppers🫑and a few cloves of garlic chopped in a pan with a little bit of olive oil💚 Add in your ground meat and continue cooking until meat is cooked through👌🏻 Season with salt, pepper & Italian seasoning, mix in half a small can of diced drained fire roasted tomatoes🍅 You could just do the whole can if you like but I knew that my kiddos wouldn’t like it with too many tomatoes😉 Next, Lightly grease a casserole dish, add a little tomato sauce first, slice up your zucchini into round medallions and layer onto sauce, sprinkle a little black pepper and grated parmesan, next top with meat mixture, add a little more fresh grated parmesan, top with fresh shredded mozzarella cheese and garnish with some fresh chopped basil. Cover with foil and bake for 40 minutes! Remove foil and bake for additional 5 minutes! 

Enjoy it just like that with a small salad for a nice low carb meal which is how I ate it😋 Or serve with some egg noodles tossed in butter, parmesan & the other half can of fire roasted tomatoes which is how my children enjoyed it😋

Gâteau aux fraises 🍰🍓🍓🍓

RECETTE gâteau 

150 gr de farine
80 gr de sucre
4 oeufs
10g de levure chimique
2 sachets de sucre vanille
50g de beurre fondu 

Dans un saladier mettre les œufs, le sucre et le sucre vanillé  battre jusqu'à que le mélange double de volume. 
Ajouter ensuite la farine et la levure tamisée et mélanger délicatement. 
Puis mettre le beurre fondu et mélanger à nouveau délicatement. 
Mettre dans un plat allant au four , avec du papier sulfurisé. 
Enfournez à 190° 
A la sortie du four laisser refroidir. 

POUR LA CRÈME :

40cl de crème (30%) bien froide
1 grosse cas et demi de mascarpone 
2 cas de sucre  glace (+ ou - selon vos goûts) 
1 sachet de fix chantilly (facultatif)

Mettre les ingrédients dans un saladier bien froid  et battre jusqu'à que le mélange  épaissis et se tient bien . Mettre dans une poche à douille.
Quand Le gâteau a bien refroidi ,  l'arroser de sirop au choix (ici c'était sucre eau et sucre vanillé) mais vous pouvez l'imbiber  de sirop de fraises que vous aurez mixé avec du sucre .
Etaler votre crème  à l'aide de votre poche à douille ou à la spatule .
Ensuite décorer avec les fraises. 
Mettre au frais jusqu'à dégustation (minimum 3h)

Quick garlicky oyster sauce ground pork with silky egg

Recipe: 
2 lbs. ground pork 
1 bulb garlic, chopped
1 large onion, diced
1 thumb ginger 
12-15 eggs, scrambled
Salt to taste
Sriracha to taste 
4 tbsp ish oyster sauce 
1 tsp chicken bouillon 

A) Over med-high heat, cook onion and ginger until aromatic. Season with salt as you go. 

B) Add ground pork, season, and let cook until the juices evaporate off. Add garlic, sriracha, oyster sauce, and chicken bouillon, making sure they make as little contact with the bottom of the pan as possible. Do Not Stir. Let sit until the pork and onion mixture caramelizes. Check progress by looking at pieces on the outer most edge of the pan. 

C) Once the pork and onion are caramelized (crusty and browned), turn the heat to high and let it sit for a minute. Then, stir everything together quickly. After combining, turn the heat off and continue mixing for another minute. Mix in softly scrambled eggs and serve over rice.

Crispy and crunchy Air Fryer 🥒 Zucchini Fries 🍟 are healthier substitute to the regular fries. It’s oil free and a crowd pleaser appetizer!
🌟
Recipe:

Ingredients:
Zucchini 

Batter:
Chickpea flour
Oregano 
Cayenne pepper 
Salt
Plant milk

Others:
Panko crumbs 

Directions:
1. Cut zucchini so the slices look like fries. 
2. Make a smooth batter in a large bowl. 
3. Toss zucchini slices into the batter and roll generously in panko crumb. 
4. Place them in single layer in air fryer basket and air fry at 350 degree for 10 minutes or until crispy.

🧄 ~ A G L I O ~ E ~ O L I O ~ 🧄

Simply means Spaghetti with Oil & Garlic. This is such a simple but beautifully delicate & delicious dish.

✨ CALLING ALL PASTA LOVERS ✨

Serves 2
Ingredients- 

- 6 tbsp extra Virgin Olive Oil @bertollioliveoiluk for me!
- 8 garlic cloves finely sliced
- 200g pasta- spaghetti or linguine
- Handful fresh parsley, finely chopped
- Salt, 1/2 Tsp
- 1/2 Tsp Black pepper- fresh ground
- Parmesan- (optional 50-80g)

In a pan add cold water heavily salted and bring to a boil. 

In a large non stick frying pan add the oil lightly heat, the key to this dish is to slowly bring the garlic to temperature without burning and allowing it to go lightly golden brown. Add the sliced garlic and ensure it doesn’t sizzle, just a low heat is fine. 

Add the pasta to the salted water and boil.
Once your kitchen smells like an authentic Italian restaurant or my dads kitchen 🧄 (extra garlic on everything) add the cooked pasta directly from the pan so it brings with it the salted pasta water, also add the freshly chopped parsley, salt, pepper & grated parmesan.

Turn off the heat and gently fold the pasta until the liquid emulsifies and goes creamy and delicious, add more pasta water if needed. 

Parmesan isn’t traditional, but sure as hell is an incredible addition and one I wouldn’t miss, especially if you’re having a glass of red with it 🤤🍷🍴

This one is bowl licking good. 

Much Love,
Jade x

Mamaliguta cu edamame si oua prajite

Repost @kitchenjunglebyh 

Un mic dejun sățios, plin de proteine, vitamine și culori surprins în razele minunate ale soarelui

Ce avem aic???

Avem o mămăliguță mai altfel
Câteva edamame prăjite în unt aromat
Ouă de găină prăjite/ ouă de prepeliță

Cum preparăm?

Rețeta de mămăliguță am mai postat-o de cateva ori în feed. Rețeta din dimineața aceasta este un mic "spin off" inspirat de aceasta cât și de una din rețetele @andreea_dutia

Mămăliguța: 1 cană apă, 1/4 cană mălai, 1 cub unt, 20g cașcaval ras sau parmezan, 300g protein cottage chesse, sare

( la mine asta reprezintă 2 porții cine dorește mai mult dublează sau triplează cantitățile)

Punem apa cu sarea la fiert. Când dă în clocot adăugăm mălaiul în ploaie timp în care amestecăm continuu. O fierbem până ajunge la consistența dorită. O luăm de pe foc și adăugăm în ea untul, cașcavalul și brânza cottage. ( de obicei în acest punct adăugam și un ou fiert zdrobit... De data asta le-am prăjit și am folosit ouă de prepeliță)

Pentru edamame: topim untul și prăjim în el puțin rozmarin tocat mărunt, cimbru verde, 1 frunză salvie, fulgi chilli. În acest ulei prăjim edamamele pentru 1-3 min.

Ouăle le prăjim tot în puțin unt.

Cum le servim ???

Punem un strat de mămăligă, un strat edamame, ouăle și decorăm cu pătrunjel verde tocat, fulgi chilli și parmezan/cașcaval răzuit

Enjoy!!!

P. S. rețeta prezentată se poate consuma evident și la prânz sau cină

As-tu déjà testé le pesto de courgette jaune ? 
Au menu : pâtes au pesto de courgettes jaunes
Les ingrédients : pour 2👩‍❤️‍👨
200g de pâtes
🌟pour le pesto : 1 courgette jaune coupée en dés, 2 càs d'huile d'olive, 1 gousse d'ail, 10 feuilles de basilic, 10g de pignons de pin, sel, poivre 
La préparation :
1️⃣Dans une poêle huilée, faire dorer les dés de courgettes. Saler et poivrer. Réserver.
2️⃣Dans le bol du mixeur, mettre les dés de courgettes avec l'ail, les pignons, le basilic et le fromage. Mixer par à coups puis verser en deux fois l'huile d'olive.  Saler et poivrer. 
Si le pesto est épais, vous pouvez le diluer avec une à deux louches d'eau de cuisson des pâtes.
3️⃣Cuire les pâtes.
4️⃣Mélanger les pâtes avec le pesto.
5️⃣ Servir avec de la feta émiettée (ou un autre fromage) et quelques tomates cerise.

You’ll have so MUCH-ROOM in your heart for this Baked Creamy MUSH-Room! 💓😍

Baked Creamy Mushrooms Recipe:
Butter - 3 tbsp + For greasing 
Garlic (finely chopped) - 1 tbsp
Onion (finely chopped) - 1 no
Thyme (finely chopped) - 1 tsp
Mushroom (diced) - 400 grams
Maida - ¼ Cup
Milk - 500 ml
Salt - ¼ tsp
Black Pepper Powder - A pinch
Cheese (grated) - ¼ Cup
Bread (cubes) - 10 - 15 nos
Mozzarella Cheese (grated) - ½ Cup

Cooking Instructions:

1. Heat a pan, and add butter. Let it melt
2. Add the chopped garlic and saute till it turns light brown
3. Add the onions and thyme and saute till it turns translucent
4. Add the mushrooms and saute for 3-4 minutes.
5. Add maida and mix till the mushrooms are coated with the maida and mix it till the maida is rid of the raw flavour
6. Add and mix till the maida is dissolved in the milk and keep mixing it till the mixture starts to thicken
7. Add salt, pepper, and fresh cream and mix it well. 
8. Add grated cheese finally and mix well. Bring the mixture to a soft boil
9. Transfer the mixture to an oven-safe bowl
10. Add bread cubes to it and press it in a little.
11. Top it off with mozzarella and bake it in the oven till the cheese turns brown

Ce ziceti de un chec cu crema de fistic, cu afine si picatele de ciocolata? Pregatiti-va pentru cea mai simpla si mai faina reteta de chec. E gata in 40 de minute cu tot cu timpul de coacere. 😉
Save/comment/❤️

Ingrediente
2 oua
2 lingurite zdravene de miere de albine
40 ml ulei neutru
200 g pasta de fistic indulcita
80 ml lapte
160 g faina de prajituri
1 praf de sare
4 g praf de copt
40 g picatele de ciocolata
40 g afine

Intai de toate preincalzim cuptorul la 180 de grade apoi facem aluatul. 

Intr-un vas incapator amestecam toate ingredientele umede pana se omogenizeaza bine apoi adaugam ingredientele uscate cernute. Omogenizam si turnam in tava tapetata cu hartie de copt. Deasupra presaram afinele spalate si uscate bine. 

Se coace la 170 de grade pentru aproximativ 30 de minute. Testul cu scobitoarea e de ajutor. 

Crema de fistic in combinatie cu ciocolata si cu afinele e de vis. Nu ratati reteta asta ca nu exista una mai simpla. In loc de pasta de fistic se poate folosi inclusiv unt de arahide indulcit.

Most health bars have the same or more sugar than a big chocolate chip cookie! ⁠
⁠
I'm not trying to make you feel bad, it isn't easy because these health bars look so wholesome but in reality most of them are high in sugars which means:⁠
⁠
💫 You'll likely be hungry again soon after eating 💫⁠
💫 Your body stores high blood sugar in the fat cells 💫⁠
💫 Your cortisol can be spiked from the high sugar 💫⁠
⁠
If you are buying health bars, aim for ones that have less than 5g of sugar per serving, it'll be more gentle on your blood sugar in the long run. ⁠

.

Chili Chicken 
.
.
.
.
.
.
Preparation Time: 15mins
Cooking Time: 30mins
Serves: 2
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
Ingredients 
For Marinade 
250gms Chicken Breast, cut into cubes 
¼ tsp Black Pepper Powder 
Salt, to taste 
4 tbsp Corn Flour 
4 tbsp Refined Flour
For Sauce 
1 tbsp Oil 
2 tbsp Garlic, chopped 
1 tbsp Ginger, chopped 
2 tsp Chili paste, (2 Green chilies + 2 tsp Vinegar) 
½ Cup Onion, diced
2 tbsp Soy Sauce
1 tbsp Red Chili Sauce
2 tsp Vinegar 
Salt & pepper powder, to taste
1 tsp Corn flour, (mixed in 2 tbsp water)
½ Cup Green onion, chopped 
Other Ingredients 
Oil, for deep frying 
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
Process 
•	Marinate the chicken with given ingredients and keep aside for 5mins. 
•	Heat oil for deep frying. Deep fry the chicken till golden and crispy. Keep aside. 
•	Now for the sauce, heat oil in a wok. Saute garlic, ginger till fragrant. 
•	Add in chili paste, onion and saute. Add soy sauce, red chili sauce, vinegar and mix well. 
•	Season with salt and pepper and drop in fried chicken. Add corn flour mixture and mix well. 
•	Lastly add green onion and turn off the flame. 
•	Garnish with fresh coriander.

Frog Eye Salad
Ingredients
1 cup sugar
2 tablespoons all-purpose flour
1/2 teaspoon salt
1-3/4 cups unsweetened pineapple juice
2 large eggs, lightly beaten
1 tablespoon lemon juice
1 package (16 ounces) acini di pepe pasta
3 cans (11 ounces each) mandarin oranges, drained
2 cans (20 ounces each) pineapple chunks, drained
1 can (20 ounces) crushed pineapple, drained
1 cup miniature marshmallows
1 cup sweetened shredded coconut
1 carton (12 ounces) frozen whipped topping, thawed
Maraschino cherries, optional

Directions
In a small saucepan, combine sugar, flour and salt. Gradually stir in pineapple juice. Bring to a boil, stirring constantly. Stir a small amount of hot mixture into eggs; return all to the pan, stirring constantly. Bring to a gentle boil; cook and stir 2 minutes longer. Remove from the heat. Gently stir in lemon juice.
Transfer to a large bowl. Cool to room temperature without stirring. Cover surface of dressing with waxed paper; refrigerate until cooled.
Cook pasta according to package directions; drain and rinse in cold water. Place in a very large bowl; stir in oranges, pineapple, marshmallows, coconut and dressing. Fold in whipped topping. Cover and refrigerate until chilled. If desired, garnish with cherries.

Source: Taste of Home

🟩 Take your GREENS up a notch...
INGREDIENTS
6 baby Red Royale or baby white potatoes, thinly sliced
1 cup (120g) frozen peas
8 Coles Australian Free Range Eggs
80g goat’s cheese, crumbled
120g pkt Coles Australian 4 Leaf Salad
METHOD
Step 1
Heat a greased 20cm (base measurement) ovenproof non-stick frying pan over medium heat. Add one-quarter of the potato. Cook for 1 min each side or until light golden and tender. Transfer to a plate. Repeat in 3 more batches with remaining potato.
Step 2
Meanwhile, cook the peas in a medium saucepan of boiling water until tender. Drain well.
Step 3
Lightly whisk the eggs in a medium bowl. Season.
Step 4
Preheat grill on medium. Arrange half the potato over the base of the frying pan. Top with half the peas and half the goat’s cheese. Continue layering with the remaining potato, peas and goat’s cheese. Pour over the egg and gently swirl the pan to cover the potato mixture. Cook over medium heat for 6 mins or until almost set.
Step 5
Cook under grill for 5 mins or until just set. Cut into wedges. Serve with salad leaves.

Source: Taste.com.au

Almond Butter Lean Collagen Brownies🤎
•
1 cup almond butter
1 egg (or flax egg)
1/2 tsp sea salt
1/2 tsp baking soda
1/2 cup of sugar (coconut or cane)
1/2 tsp vanilla
1/2 cup of chocolate chips/chunks
1 scoop of Creamy Vanilla Whey Plexus Lean Protein powder
2 scoops of collagen peptides
•
Directions⬇️
Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Mix all ingredients except chocolate chips/chunks until smooth.
Fold in chocolate chunks + pour batter into pan (if you want perfect brownies grease pan or use parchment paper).
Bake brownies until golden dark brown – about 25 mins.
Cool brownies for at least 10 mins before cutting.

Summer time and ice cream go hand and hand! Try this amazingggg recipe for 𝐁𝐥𝐚𝐜𝐤𝐛𝐞𝐫𝐫𝐲 𝐂𝐨𝐛𝐛𝐥𝐞𝐫 𝐰𝐢𝐭𝐡 𝐜𝐫𝐞𝐚𝐦𝐲 𝐕𝐚𝐧𝐢𝐥𝐥𝐚 𝐈𝐜𝐞 𝐜𝐫𝐞𝐚𝐦‼️ 🫐🍰

𝗜𝗡𝗚𝗥𝗘𝗗𝗜𝗘𝗡𝗧𝗦⁣
½ cup of sugar 
1 tbsp of cornstarch 
1 lb blackberries 
¼ cup GOYA® Light Flavor Olive Oil
1 tsp lemon juice 
3 tbsp vegetable shortening 
1 cup flour 
1 tbsp sugar 
1 ½ tsp baking powder 
½ tsp salt 
½ cup milk 
Vanilla ice cream (to serve on side) 

𝐌𝐄𝐓𝐇𝐎𝐃
1️⃣ First, preheat the oven to 400° F. 
2️⃣ While the oven pre-heats, mix ½ cup of sugar with the cornstarch and the GOYA® Light Flavor Olive Oil. 
3️⃣ Wash the blackberries well and add them with the lemon juice. 
4️⃣ Cook on a medium heat stirring continuously with a wooden spoon so that that the mixture boils and thickens. Put to one side. 
5️⃣ In a bowl, add the butter to the flour, 1 tablespoon of sugar, baking powder and salt and beat with a mixer until fine crumbs appear in the mixture. 
6️⃣ At this point, add the milk and continue to mix. 
7️⃣ Pour the blackberry mix into an oven cake dish and spread the crumble on top making sure it is spread across the dish. 
8️⃣ Bake for 25 to 30 minutes or until golden. 
9️⃣ Remove the dish from the oven and stand to allow to cool for 5 minutes, 
🔟 Serve warm with a scoop of vanilla ice cream.

These Creamy, Lemony Cucumber Sandwiches are perfect for lunches, get togethers and parties! 🍋🥒 They’re super easy to make in advance and taste incredible! ✨

Save this post! Full recipe below! 👇

Ingredients: 

4 oz whole cream cheese, softened to room temp
2 TB chopped fresh dill
Zest and Juice of half a large lemon
Salted butter, softened for spreading on bread slices
kosher salt
freshly ground black pepper
6 slices high quality white or whole grain bread
1/2 large cucumber, seeded and thinly sliced, thoroughly dried with paper towels

Instructions: 

Combine: in a small bowl, combine cream cheese, fresh dill, lemon zest, and lemon juice. Add enough kosher salt and pepper to taste.

Assemble: butter each slice of bread (prevents sogginess.) Lay slices with butter-side-up on a work surface. Evenly distribute the cream cheese mixture onto each slice. Arrange towel-dried cucumber slices on top of the first 3 slices of bread. Top with remaining bread. Slice off the crusts. If not serving immediately, wrap tightly in cling wrap and chill for up to 24 hours.
Slice: when ready to serve, slice into 4 triangles per sandwich. Cover and chill any leftovers.

No-Bake Salted Chocolate Tahini Tart 🍫🥧⁠
.⁠
A rich, crunchy chocolate crust and silky ganache filling AND no bake time? This one is almost too good to be true.⁠
.⁠
Chocolate // Graham crackers // Tahini // Fresh fruit⁠
.⁠
Ingredients:⁠
⁠
Crust⁠
600g chocolate graham cracker crumb⁠
1/2 cup butter, melted⁠
½ tsp salt, to taste⁠
⁠
Filling⁠
10 oz chocolate, melted (dark or semi-sweet)⁠
1.5 cups full fat, 35% cream⁠
1/3 cup tahini⁠
⁠
Garnish⁠
Fresh fruit⁠
½ tsp maldon or flaky salt⁠
.⁠
Directions:⁠
⁠
For the Crust⁠
1. Melt butter and mix with graham cracker crumbs until a thick sandy mixture develops.⁠
2. Season with salt and press into a tart pan lined with parchment. Chill in the fridge.⁠
⁠
For the Filling⁠
1. In a pot, scald the cream. Remove from heat and add in the chocolate and tahini.⁠
2. Once combined, pour the mixture into the chilled tart mold.⁠
3. Place in the fridge for 45 minutes to set fully. ⁠
⁠
For the Garnish⁠
1. Garnish with fruit of your choice and finish with maldon or flaky salt.⁠
.⁠
.⁠
.⁠

Warm salad of purple sprouting broccoli, new potatoes and #ParmigianoReggiano 😍

INGREDIENTS:
- 400g New potatoes, preferably Charlotte
- 20g Hazelnuts, blanched
- 200g Purple sprouting broccoli, trimmed of its thick stalks
- ½ Red onion, thinly sliced (approx. 75g)
- 20g Parmigiano Reggiano
- 20g Flat leaf parsley, leaves picked from the stalks (big handful)
- 6 Basil leaves (2.5g)
- 1 Tarragon sprig, leaves picked (1g)
- 1 small clove garlic
- 2 anchovy fillets, from a tin (optional)
- ½ tsp Dijon mustard
- ½ Lemon, juiced, the rest kept for garnish

METHOD:
1. Boil the potatoes until cooked, approx. 15 minutes, then drain.
2. Make a garlic paste by smashing it with salt with the back of your knife. Add to the picked herbs and the anchovies and chop finely. Put in a bowl and mix with the mustard, lemon juice, olive oil and black pepper.
3. Toast the hazelnuts in a dry pan for a few minutes. Use a pestle and mortar or similar to coarsely crush the hazelnuts.
4. Heat 2 tbsp olive oil in the same frying pan. Add the broccoli and sliced onion and a splash of water. Cover and sauté/steam until broccoli cooked al dente. Remove lid and boil off any water left in pan. Season and empty into large bowl.
5. Thickly slice the potatoes and add to the pan, with a splash more olive oil if needed. Fry for a couple of minutes to reheat. Season well.
6. Add the dressing to the bowl and coat everything.

riso thai e riso integrale con farro
fagioli neri stufati con cipolla di Tropea 
salsiccia di pollo e tacchino
carne di vitello
