😂Seriously though, who can relate!? Our need for carbs when we are stressed is hardwired into us..

When we are stressed, we are spending time in a state within the nervous system called 'sympathetic' or 'fight or flight' This state is ruled by cortisol and adrenaline, your stress hormones. 

On the other side of things we have the 'parasympathetic nervous state' which is when we are relaxed, calm, not stress eating cakes. This state is ruled by dopamine and GABA, our calm, relaxed hormones. 

Just as we can have low levels of things like iron and so eat red meat or a take an iron supplement to try to boost our levels, we can have lower levels of dopamine or GABA.

These low levels can impact us more so at certain times of the month than others... Before a period/during menopause our progesterone levels are at a very low point, which means we have less GABA/Dopamine circulating than usual. So our bodies will try to 'help' us with getting us to eat cakes, carbs or chocolate which help us create a little hit of dopamine. 

While it feels good in the moment, it usually means our blood sugar sky rockets and then we end up feeling groggy, tired and grumpy when it comes back down again. High blood sugar also impacts our nervous system, so we can get a bit stuck in a cycle of sorts.

So what's a girl to do when life isn't fair and cake is the answer?! Here's a few tips:

💫 Pair sugar with protein/fat e.g. nuts, seeds
💫 Taking 4 deep breaths in, hold for 4 and release for 4 seconds engages the vagus nerve and surpasses cortisol release
💫 Consider a magnesium glycinate supplement (speak to doc first if you take any meds) 
💫 Stop having caffeine on an empty stomach - it is spiking your cortisol and contributing to your stress eating. Instead have decaf or have food first

Helloooo.... 🙋‍♀️ Veceras kolac po receptu moje komsinice 😇  Zaliveni kolac sa grizom,brzo se sprema. Jednostavan,a ukusan. Revani,kolac turskog porekla. Originalan recept je sa #youtube  Za meru sam koristila solje,od 200ml.

Prvo skuvati saft :
2 solje secera
3 solje vode
Malo limunovog soka
Vodu i secer staviti da se kuvaju,pustiti da kljuca 8-10 min. Pred kraj dodati malo limunovog soka.

Rernu ukljuciti na 180 stepeni da se ugreje.

Kolac:
3 jaja
1 solja secera
1 solja griza
1 solja jogurta
1 solja ulja
Malkice vise od 1/2 solje brasna
1 prasak za pecivo

*po zelji mozete ubaciti malo rendane limunove korice

Jaja i secer mikserom penasto umutiti,pa dodati jogurt,ulje i griz pa jos malo umutiti. Pomesati brasno i prasak za pecivo,pa sve zajedno polako jos malo umesati.

Tepsiju ili pleh za pecenje pomastiti i sipati masu i pravac rerna 😅
Kolac peci oko 25-30 min,ako niste sigurni znate za onaj trik sa  cackalicom 😅 
Pecen kolac izrezati,pa zaliti prohladjenim saftom i ostaviti da se ohladi. Po zelji posuti pistacima,orasima,kokosovim ljuspicama....

INGREDIENTS
12 boneless, skinless chicken thighs (about 950g | 2lbs)
Salt and pepper to taste
2 tbsp coconut oil
2 cups broccoli florets
1 cup light chicken stock
2 tbsp balsamic vinegar
1 tbsp Dijon mustard
1 tbsp tapioca starch
1 tsp chili pepper flakes
.
.
INSTRUCTIONS
Sprinkle the chicken thighs with salt and pepper and then melt the coconut oil in a large, skillet set over high heat. When the pan is hot enough, add the pieces of chicken, nice-looking side down, and cook them without moving them for about 4 minutes, until they turn opaque about half way up and develop a nice golden crust. Flip the pieces of chicken and cook them for another 3 to 4 minutes, until the meat is cooked all the way through and the juices run clear. Remove to a plate.
Put the skillet back over the heat source, lower the heat to medium and add the broccoli. Cook it for about 3 minutes, until slightly softened.

Meanwhile, mix the chicken stock, vinegar, mustard, chili pepper flakes and tapioca starch together in a large glass measuring cup or other container, preferably one that is equipped with a spout.
Pour this over the broccoli as soon as it’s cooked to your liking; bring to the boil and continue cooking until the sauce thickens

Enjoying veggie loaded nachos from Everyday Celebrations from Scratch, with Maria Provenzano. Fun concept pairing crafts with cooking, and great tasting delicious food. ⁠
⁠
 Maria is a lover of all things crafty and is obsessed with cooking and feeding those around her. She is self-taught--and mom-taught, taking inspiration from the most imaginative, organized, detail-oriented person she knows: her mom! ⁠
⁠
The book is a combination of pairing crafts with cooking to build in celebrations and a festive vibe to everyday living. I love simple ideas like placemats on Takeout Thursdays. I can totally see the projects both as celebrations as to engage kids or just celebrate life.⁠
Each section of the book provides inspiration for both food and do-it-yourself (DIY) projects, so you can invest minimum time for maximum impact!⁠
⁠
So many wonderful recipes, the first one I tried here was her veggie loaded nachos. I subbed eggplant for the sweet potatoes as I have a lot of good eggplant around. Served these with a side of guacamole, great diner and a new fun addition to my repertoire. I have a few more fun dishes I want to try, including the lemony basil pesto, which is recently demoed. Her blog is gull of amazing and fun ideas (linked here). Stay tuned for more fun from this cookbook.⁠

Ingredients:

1/2 lb. farfalle
1 medium yellow onion, finely chopped
1 tsp olive oil
3 large garlic cloves, minced
4 plant based sausages (396 g)
1 tsp kosher salt
1/2 tsp black pepper
1 tsp dried parsley
1/2 tsp dried oregano
1 cup (packed) baby spinach
1 cup canned crushed tomatoes
1 cup dairy free heavy cream

Instructions:

Cook farfalle in salted water according to package directions, reserving 1/4 cup of the cooking water prior to draining.

Meanwhile, preheat large pan on medium heat. Add onions and oil, cook on medium low for 10 min, adding 1/2 cup water to prevent burning if needed and stirring periodically. Add minced garlic and crumble in the sausages. Stir, add all the seasonings, and cook for 6 to 8 min, stirring periodically, until starting to brown. Add remaining ingredients and cook 2 to 3 min, stirring as spinach wilts. Add pasta, stir, add pasta cooking water if desired. Serve with red chili flakes and basil if desired.

🍪 @mrs.nancyhenning Cookie Dough Week!🍪 

✨It’s important to have a basic brown sugar cookie dough recipe that you can adapt easily to other recipes. Think different mix-ins, a good balance of sugar & salt. 

✨I personally like mine to taste a little more like vanilla than most.✨

✨What’s important is that a dough like this can freeze easily so it can be prepped in advance & placed in the fridge for up to 2 days, anything longer may dry it out. Or you can freeze it up to 6 months. Personally, I make the dough as I want to cook it, with the add-ins mixed in. Then, I roll into balls & place on a cookie sheet & transfer to freezer for 2 hours. Don’t forget to take them out and place in a sealed freezer bag with date written on the bag. 

✨You do not have to thaw frozen cookie dough! Just add an additional 2 minutes to your cooking time & you will still get a wonderfully chewy cookie!

Roasted Eggplant with Halloumi, Yogurt & Fresh Herbs✨
If you're looking for a quick and flavorful lunch idea, I’ve got you!
This easy dish made with some of my most favorite ingredients. Eggplant, halloumi, yogurt, sumac and fresh herbs. I mean, name a better duo than halloumi and eggplant! All the textures and flavors goes very well together and sumac is here to bring some tang to this dish. 
📍I leave the ingredients list for you here and you can get the full recipe in my website. Link in Bio.

-Ingredients For Roasted Eggplant:

1 large eggplant
3 tablespoons olive oil
1 teaspoon salt
1/2 teaspoon freshly ground pepper
1 teaspoon fresh thyme leaves

-To Serve:

100 gram halloumi (cut into 1 inch cubes)
1 cup greek yogurt
2 cloves garlic (minced)
1/4 of medium red onion (thinly sliced)
1/2 cup fresh parsley (roughly chopped)
1/4 cup fresh dill (roughly chopped)
1/4 cup fresh mint (roughly chopped)
2 tablespoons sumac
1 tablespoon fresh lime juice
1 tablespoon olive oil
1 teaspoon chili flakes (optional)
Flaky salt to taste
Pita bread for serving (optional)

Spaghetti bolognaise

Aveți nevoie de
Spaghetti - pe care le preparați conform instrucțiunilor de pe ambalaj

Pentru sosul bolognaise:
250g carne de vită tocată
1 ceapă tocată
1 morcov tocat mărunt
2 căței de usturoi zdrobiți
1 lg ulei de măsline
2 fire rozmarin tocat mărunt 
1 leg de busuioc verde tocat
Sare și piper după gust
1/4 lgț fulgi ardei iute
1lgț oregano uscat
2 frunze dafin
100ml vin roșu sec
1 conservă roșii cuburi
2lg pastă tomate
150g roșii cherry tăiate în jumătăți sau sferturi
1/2 lgț scorțișoară
 
Parmezan pentru servit

1. Încingem ulei într-o cratiță încăpătoare.

2. Călim în ulei morcovii, ceapă, usturoiul și rozmarinul pentru 5-10min, cât să se înmoaie legumele.

3. Adăugăm carnea tocată și gătim până se evaporă apă ce și-o lasă ( amestecând din când în când)

4. Se adaugă restul ingredientelor și puțină apă ( 100-200ml), se amestecă bine, se acoperă cratița și se fierbe pe foc mic timp de 75min timp în care amestecăm frecvent.

Împărțim pastele în boluri, adăugăm peste sosul și parmezan răzuit. 

Savurăm alături de un vin bun. 

Enjoy!!!

Recette du jour ! 😋 Tarte chocolat et amande ! 🍫💐

Voici une belle recette de dessert qui ravira les fan de chocolat ! Rien de plus simple en préparation et en ingrédients ! ✨🫶🏼
Le lait utilisé était du lait d’amande provenant du pot de crème d’amande de chez @mandaya_fr 

⏲ Temps de préparation : 10min
Temps de cuisson : 20min

🥧 Ingrédients :
- 200g de chocolat 🍫 
- 300ml de lait (de vache ou d’amande)
- 1 pâte feuilletée ou brisée
- Des amandes 

👩🏼‍🍳 Préparation : 
1. Étaler la pâte feuilletée sur un plat à tarte allant au four et faire des trous à la fourchette
2. Faire chauffer la pâte seul 20min a 180º (piquer les trois si besoin pour garder une pâte plate)
3. Casser en petits morceaux le chocolat dans un bol et ajouter un peu de lait puis le faire fondre au micro-onde 
4. Une fois fondu, remuer pour ne plus avoir de grumeaux et ajouter la fin du lait pour avoir un beau liquide
5. Une fois la pâte cuite, verser le chocolat fondu dessus et casser quelques amandes pour la déco 
6. Mettre au frais 3-4h et déguster bien frais ! 

Vous pouvez à présent réaliser cette superbe recette de tarte au chocolat ! Puis n’hésitez pas à partager vos réalisations en identifiant le compte ! ✨📷🌈💐

tagliare a rondelle le zucchine , passarle nella farina 00 oppure quella per la pastellatura.
passaggio successivo mettere una pentola con olio sul fuoco vivo e far friggere le zucchine .

ottima ricetta per un contorno.

Polenta porridge with hazelnuts and banana is a great way to mix up your breakfast routine!

If you don’t have 45 minutes to make breakfast, that’s ok. It makes for a great meal prep dish!

If you’ve never tried polenta this is a great starter recipe. It’s an Italian porridge that has a low-fat content and high in complex carbs.

This polenta porridge with hazelnuts and banana is easy to make, nutritious, and extremely tasty! The flavors combine perfectly into a delicious bowl of amazing goodness. You can also substitute the banana with other berries or fruits of your choice.

✨ Prep Time: 5 min | Cook Time: 40 min | Serves: 4 ✨

Ingredients
2 cups of water
1/4 teaspoon salt
1/4 teaspoon cinnamon
1/2 cup coarse stone-ground polenta
3 tablespoons honey, divided
3/4 cup of plain greek yogurt
1/2 teaspoon vanilla extract
1 banana for topping (blueberries, raspberries, kiwi, and blackberries are also good choices)
½ cup of natural roasted hazelnuts

Instructions
1️⃣Bring the water to a boil.
2️⃣Stir in the salt and slowly whisk in the polenta. Keep stirring so that no clumps form.
3️⃣Add 1 1/2 tablespoons of honey.
4️⃣Reduce heat to a simmer.
5️⃣Simmer for at least 30-35 minutes, stirring occasionally.
6️⃣When the polenta begins to pull away from the sides as you stir, then you know it is done.
7️⃣Remove from heat and whisk in 3/4 cup of yogurt, cinnamon, and the vanilla.
8️⃣Top with remaining honey, sliced banana (or berries of choice), and natural roasted hazelnuts.

If you are looking to bring a yummy pasta salad to the next outdoor summer BBQ, try out this amazing Grilled Ratatouille Pasta Salad!

Ingredients: 

∙ 2 medium zucchini (about 1½ lb.), halved lengthwise
∙ About 1 lb Adagio® Eggplants , cut into 1" wedges
∙ ¾ cup extra-virgin olive oil, divided
∙ 2½ tsp. kosher salt, divided
∙ 1 tsp. freshly ground black pepper, divided
∙ 10 oz. penne or casarecce pasta
∙ 1 large or 2 medium Heirloom or Virtuoso® Beefsteak Tomatoes (about 1 lb.), cut into 1" pieces
∙ 8 oz. Ciliegini (mini fresh mozzarella balls), drained, halved
∙ 2 Tbsp. white balsamic or white wine vinegar
∙ 1 Tbsp. thyme leaves
∙ 1 cup basil leaves

Instructions:

1. Prepare a grill for medium heat. Toss zucchini, eggplant, and ¼ cup oil on a rimmed baking sheet; season with 1 tsp. salt and ½ tsp. pepper. Grill, turning often, until steamy, tender, and charred all over, 8–12 minutes. Return to the baking sheet and let cool.

2. Cook pasta according to package directions.

3. Slice grilled vegetables into bite-size pieces and transfer to a large bowl. Add tomato, cheese, vinegar, thyme, and 1½ tsp. salt, ½ tsp. pepper, and ½ cup oil and mix to combine. Drain pasta and immediately add to the bowl with vegetables. Mix well to combine, then top with basil.

🥑 No Cook Burrito Bowl with Spiced Lentil Taco Meat ✨ 
By @plantbasedrd 

🌿 Follow @almost_vegan77 for daily delicious plant-based recipe shares 🍅🥦😁
----------

#Repost @plantbasedrd

No fancy equipment needed and if you use a can of lentils this comes together in 20 minutes. I love to prep these lentils in advance for the week because they are so easy to sprinkle into meals and keep well. And if you don’t want to chop veggies for your bowl just swap for your favorite bagged salad mix and top with the lentil walnut taco meat. 😌

Lentil Walnut ‘Meat’
1, 15 oz can small brown or black lentils, rinsed and drained (salted can preferred)
1/2 cup chopped unsalted walnuts
1/3 cup chopped roasted unsalted sunflower seeds
1 1/2 tbsp adobo sauce from a can of chipotle peppers
1 tsp soy sauce
1 tsp each garlic powder, smoked paprika, chili powder
1/2 tsp ground cumin
1/2 tsp onion powder
Salt and pepper to taste

Salad Base
1 head Romaine Lettuce, shredded
1 cup cherry tomatoes, halved or quartered
1 cup frozen fire roasted corn, thawed
1 red bell pepper, diced
1/3 cup cilantro, roughly chopped (optional)
Juice of half a lime

Chipotle Yogurt Dressing
1/4 cup plain, unsweetened plant-based yogurt
1 1/2 tbsp adobo sauce from a can of chipotle peppers
2 tsp maple syrup
Zest and juice of half a lime

Seasoned Lentils. Add your lentils to a small bowl with the chopped walnuts, sunflower seeds, adobo sauce, soy sauce, spices and toss together then adjust salt to your liking.

Salad Base. To a large salad bowl or mixing bowl add the lettuce, tomatoes, corn, bell pepper and cilantro then season well with a pinch of salt, pepper and lime juice then toss together to combine.

Chipotle Yogurt Dressing. Add the remaining dressing ingredients to a cup and mix well until smooth then add a pinch of salt to taste

Assemble. Add the seasoned lentils on top of the salad base, then add the yogurt dressing before serving.

Need an easy brunch recipe? This Plant-Based🌱 Breakfast Casserole is so simple and so tasty! It’s a great vegan recipe for brunch and it feeds at least 8 people. And the key to this dish, is the savory kick from the plant-based @eatlocafood LOCA Foods potato queso! It is just such a delicious recipe! So whether or not your guests are vegetarian, vegan, or meat-eaters, they’ll enjoy this dish! 

Get these ingredients, and try this recipe for your breakfast tomorrow, it won't disappoint!

✨Gluten-Free Plant-Based Breakfast Casserole Recipe:✨
INGREDIENTS:
▢Gluten-free nonstick cooking spray
▢1 (30-ounce) package of frozen gluten-free hash browns
▢1 onion, diced
▢1 red bell pepper, seeded, deveined, and diced
▢8 ounces sliced mushrooms, baby Bellas (cremini), or white
▢2 cups chopped kale or spinach
▢1½ jars @eatlocafood  Potato Queso, mild or spicy
▢Smoked paprika
US Customary - Metric

INSTRUCTIONS:
1. Preheat the oven to 350 degrees. Spray a 9x12-inch casserole dish with cooking spray.

2. In a large bowl, combine the hashbrowns with the onion, bell pepper, mushrooms, and kale. Add the queso and mix well. Pour into the prepared dish and sprinkle with paprika. Bake for 30-40 minutes or until everything is hot.

☆ Pâtes aux courgettes et citron 🍋
.
Les pâtes au citron, qui connais ?🖐🏻😋
Si c'est pas le cas, je vous le recommande à 10 000, ça change et apporte un petit goût assez sympa.
Et niveau diet, vous me connaissez... Tant qu'on peut varier la diet dit oui ! 🤪
Je vous propose là un plat complet auquel vous pourrez ajouter un œuf mollet, un poisson ou une viande, n'importe 🍳
.
Aller je vous partage la recette, c'est vraiment pas compliqué :
.
➡️ Ingrédients (pour 2 personnes):
.
- 200 g de spaghetti crues
- 400 g de courgettes ou 4 courgettes
- 1 citron jaune zeste et jus
- 80 g de parmesan
- sel, poivre
- 2 c.s d'huile d'olive vierges extra
.
.
➡️ Méthode :
.
🍋 Laver et couper en rondelle les courgettes. Les faire revenir à la poêle avec 1 c.s d'huile d'olive.
🍋 Mettre de l'eau à bouillir pour les pâtes et y laisser infuser le zeste de citron. Ajouter les pâtes.
🍋 Une fois les pâtes cuites, les égoutter, les disposer dans un récipient et y ajouter : 1c.s d'huile d'olive, les courgettes, le reste de zeste de citron s'il y a, le jus du citron, sel, poivre et parmesan.
🍋 Servir chaud avec un peu de parmesan râpé sur le dessus 😋
.
.
.
.
.

Today’s recipe of the day is an effort to perfect perfection 🙌 And to be honest, the Greek salad 🥗 needs no real adjustments when the ingredients are so good. 
So let’s think of this more of a way to enhance what is already excellent with ingredients that are fresh, local, and delicious! 

Capers are really a great addition to any salad - the ones from my shop come from Santorini, where they grow wild everywhere, jutting out from stone walls and sprouting along craggy coasts. I’ve also included caper leaves 🌱 in this salad, a bit more subtle in flavor than the capers themselves. And pistachios🥜 from Aegina bring a pleasantly salty crunch to each bite!

I’ve also added 2 fruits to this salad: watermelon 🍉 and peaches 🍑 which are both in-season at the same time as the rest of the Greek salad. It’s a hint of sweetness that perfectly compliments the fresh acidity from the tomatoes, the briny capers and leaves, and the salty crunch of pistachio 👌

🤩Find the recipe at the link in my bio!

✨QUICK GREEK CHICKEN FLATBREADS ✨

Post by @weighlesswith_jess

Okay I won’t lie to you, this is barely a recipe but I made it for lunch today - then tasted the chicken and it was just super delish, so I had to quickly film it and share it 😂

📍 Serves 1
📍 535 Calories & 54.9g Protein

✨150g Chicken Breast, diced
✨1 flatbread
✨1/2tbsp Oregano
✨1/2tbsp Garlic Powder
✨25g Feta Cheese
✨50g Cucumber, sliced
✨40g Tzatziki
✨1tbsp Balsamic Glaze (optional!)

- Firstly fry off your chicken with a little olive oil spray, your oregano, garlic powder and a good pinch of salt and pepper; allow to cook for about 6 minutes over a medium heat or until fully cooked through.

- While your chicken is cooking, pop your flatbread under the grill for a couple of minutes or until slightly toasted.

- Once your chicken is cooked you can assemble! Spread out your tzatziki onto your flatbread, then add your cucumber and chicken, crumble over your feta and finally drizzle with your balsamic glaze.

And that is literally it! I told you it was hardly a recipe 😂 But it was so delicious and absolutely packed with protein too 🙌🏼

Let me know if you try it Lovelies 🥰

This Chocolate Pancake  is a must try for all chocolate lovers. 

Use Trust range of sugars for the perfect balance of sweetness and taste.

Repost @homecookingshow

Ingredients:
-Maida - 1 1/3 Cup
-Cocoa Powder - 4 Tbsp
-Baking Powder - 2 Tsp
-Sugar - 3 Tbsp
-Chocolate Chip - 2 Tbsp
-Salt - 1/4 Tsp
-Egg - 1 No.
-Milk - 1 Cup
-Melted Butter - 1/4 Cup
-Vanilla Essence - 1/4 Tsp
-Milk - 1/4 Cup
-Butter

Chocolate ganache
-Fresh Cream - 1/2 Cup
-Milk - 1/4 Cup
-Semi-sweet Cooking Chocolate - 100 Gms

Method:
-To make pancakes
-In a medium bowl whisk together egg until creamy. Add in milk and melted butter, and whisk until combined well.
-In another bowl whisk dry ingredients and add them into the wet ingredients. Whisk until combined well. It will be a thick batter. Fold in chocolate chips.
- Heat a pan over medium heat and either spread a little butter over it.
- Scoop the batter onto the pan using a 1/4 cup for each pancake.
- Cook until you see bubbles on the top, for about 1 minute or so.
-Flip them over and cook for another 1 minute.
-Transfer to a serving plate and repeat with the remaining batter.
-Serve pancakes with chocolate ganache

To make the Chocolate Ganache
-Heat heavy cream and milk in a saucepan.
-Add chocolate chunks and stir well until it turns into a smooth and silky ganache.
-Wait until it reaches room temperature before pouring it over pancakes

Spinach Puffs
Ingredients
1 package (17.3 ounces) frozen puff pastry, thawed
1 package (10 ounces) frozen chopped spinach, thawed and squeezed dry
4 ounces cream cheese, softened
1/2 cup shredded mozzarella cheese
1/4 cup crumbled feta cheese
2 large eggs, divided use
2 garlic cloves, minced
1/2 teaspoon pepper
1/4 teaspoon salt

Directions
Preheat oven to 400°. Unfold puff pastry; cut each sheet into 12 sections. Place in greased mini muffin cups, pressing gently onto bottoms and up sides, allowing corners to point up.
In a large bowl, stir together spinach, cream cheese, mozzarella, feta, 1 egg, garlic, pepper and salt. Spoon 1 tablespoon into each cup. Bring pastry corners together and pinch to seal. In a small bowl, beat remaining egg. Brush over pastry edges. Bake until puffed and golden brown, about 20 minutes.

Source: Taste of Home

overnight oats 🍯 if you’re wanting some easy and deLISH breakfast inspiration, you need these overnight oats at the top of your list! I’ve been making it in 3-day batches and I can’t get enough 🤤 recipe below - brands tagged for reference!

Overnight oats (makes 3 portions)

Ingredients:
- 1.5 cups @quakeroatsuk oats
- 2 scoops unflavoured or vanilla @bulk protein powder
- 1/2 tsp cinnamon
- 1.5-2 cups milk of choice (I use @alpro) 
- 2/3 cup greek yoghurt
- 2 tbsp chia seeds
- maple syrup to taste (I used about 1 tbsp)
- 1 tsp vanilla essence (omit if using vanilla protein)
- 1/4 cup dark chocolate chips

method:
- mix together the oats, protein powder and cinnamon
- add the rest of the ingredients and mix together until we’ll combined
- pour into an airtight container (or multiple if you want them in pre-prepped portions)
- store in the fridge for up to three days. Serve topped with fresh strawberries 🍓 and @pipandnut peanut butter

Ayam Masak Merah

1/2 chicken
3 shallots
2 garlic
1 lemongrass
3 sekawan (Cinnamon Stick, Cloves and Cardamom)
1 tbsp chilli paste
3 tbsp tomato sauce
2 tbsp chilli sauce
1/4 cup evaporated milk
1/4 cup green peas 

1. Fry chicken with salt and turmeric. Set aside. 
2. Blend shallots and garlic. Sauté with lemongrass until fragrant. 
3. Add in chilli paste with 1 tsp of sugar. Cook until the oil separates (pecah minyak). Add water if needed. 
4. Add in tomato and chilli sauces with some water. Simmer until sauce thickens. 
5. Add in evaporated milk and mix until homogenous before adding in the fried chicken. 
6. Add in green peas before turning off the heat.

Instant pick-me-up

Are you feeling stressed, anxious, tired or all of the above? How about an instant pick-me-up in the form of a detoxifying juice to help beat the holiday blues?

Sometimes we don't have time or the appetite to eat all the healthy vegetables and fruits, so freshly made juices can be a brilliant addition to a healthy diet.

Beetroots, carrots and pineapples are excellent ingredients for a quick pick-me-up juice, and they are all packed full of nutrients and deliciousness.

Beetroots are a good source of vitamins and minerals, such as folate, manganese, iron, vitamin C, boron, silica and potassium. Furthermore, they are high in several beneficial plant compounds, mainly betaine, vulgaxanthin and inorganic nitrates (which are associated with reduced blood pressure). Not only can beetroots lower blood pressure, they can also improve oxygen use, stamina and exercise performance. Beetroots are also high in fibre, which is a good thing, but please note that they also have FODMAPs, which for some can cause digestive problems.

Carrots are also packed full of nutrients and are a good source of beta carotene, vitamin K1, fibre, potassium and antioxidants. Carrots have many health benefits and they have been linked to weight loss, lowered cholesterol and improved eye health.

Then we have pineapples - an ubebu favourite! They are also loaded with nutrients and vitamins, such as vitamin C, manganese, copper and vitamin B6. Additionally, they contain disease-fighting antioxidants and they have been found to ease digestion and arthritis and boost immunity.

Bon appetit!

Finally got round to making baba ganoush! Not sure why but I thought it was going to be way more effort than it was. TASTED UNBELIEVABLE 🤤 no blender needed. 

Ingredients: 
2 aubergines 
2 minced garlic cloves 
2 tablespoons lemon juice 
1/4 cup tahini 
1/3 cup olive oil 
2 tbsp chopped flat leaf parsley
1/4 tsp cumin 
Salt n peps 
Sprinkle of paprika 

Method:
~ preheat oven to 230 degrees c 
~ chop your aubergines in half lengthwise and brush cut sides with olive oil 
~ place them skin side up on baking paper lined tray and bake in oven for 35-40 mins 
~ when done, scoop out aubergine flesh and strain flesh to get rid of liquid 
~ put in bowl, add garlic and lemon juice, and whisk with a fork to break down the aubergine 
~ add tahini and stir till combined 
~ while stirring, slowly drizzle in olive oil 
~ once all broken down and mixed together, add in salt, cumin and parsley 
~ add more lemon juice to taste 
~ transfer to a pretty bowl and drizzle with more olive oil and a sprinkle of paprika and parsley 

Voila! I chopped up some pitta breads and roasted them in olive oil, salt n peps and rosemary to scoop up the deliciousness with.

I’m a fritter lover… save this post to try this version - Fennel Seed, Courgette, Corn and Smoked Chilli 

This makes for the perfect speedy and satisfying dinner alongside a fresh green salad 🍽 

Any left overs? Pack them for lunch or warm them up another evening (keep in the fridge for up to 4 days) ✅ 

Want something gluten free? Simply substitute the flour for either self raising GF flour, almond mehl or chickpea flour 😍

Ok enough chit chat - you’ll need ✨ 

1 tsp fennel seeds 
2 large courgettes, grated 
2 spring onions, finely sliced
2 tsp baking powder 
1 tsp salt 
400 grams corn kennels 
2 tbsp coriander, finely chopped
1 1/2 tsp smoked chilli flakes
3/4 cup flour
1/2 cup breadcrumbs 
1 cup canola oil for frying 
Coriander, lime and mayo to serve 

Method
In a morale and pestle, crush the fennel seeds.

Place the grated courgettes, spring onions, salt, corn kennels, coriander, crushed fennel seeds and smoked chilli flakes into a large mixing bowl. Mix well.

Add the flour and breadcrumbs along with 1 tablespoon of water to help emulsify.

Heat 1/3 of the oil in a non stick pan. Once hot and using an ice cream scoop, spoon into the oil. Fill the. Pan but do not over crowd. Press down a little too flatten so you have flat bottom but fluffy fritters. cook until golden on high heat and flip, cooking until golden and crunchy again. Remove and drain excess oil onto paper towel.

Heat another 1/3 of the oil and repeat.

To serve, place crunchy fritters onto a serving platter, mayo into a small serving bowl and I like to top with extra virgin olive oil and a sprinkle of sea salt. Finish with lime wedges and coriander

Soy Miso Beef
P 48 | F 11 | C 43
470 Calories

180g Diced Lean Beef
2tsp (10ml) Soy Sauce
1tsp (5g) Miso Paste
5g Sesame Oil
1tsp Fresh Ginger (minced)
1 x Garlic (minced)
70g Bok Choy
40g Broccolini
125g Cooked Rice

Season beef with salt and pepper. Mix soy sauce, miso, sesame oil, ginger, and garlic together then pour over the beef and coat evenly.
Using a pan on high heat, stir fry the beef in 2 batches to ensure it cooks crispy, avoid too much liquid from over crowding in the pan. Cook for 3-5 minutes to taste. 
Set aside, clean the wok, then on high heat stir fry the broccolini for 4 minutes. Add the bok choy and a splash of water, cook for 1 minute for perfect crunchy vegetables.
Serve with rice and top with spring onions/chilli to taste.

Chimichurri Crispy Potatoes 🥔 by @alwayshungryinlondon

Smokey bites of potato heaven with a spicy chimichurri sauce. 

Potatoes:
10 baby potatoes
1tbsp olive oil
1/2tsp cumin seeds
1tsp sweet smoked paprika 
pinch of sea salt 

Chimichurri: 
1 fat clove of garlic
1 red chilli
Handful of parsley 
2tsp chopped fresh oregano 
Salt and pepper 
Extra virgin olive oil & white vinegar 

Preheat the oven to 200 degrees c. Parboil the potatoes. Place potatoes on baking tray and lightly crush them. Add the oil and spices. Roast for 20 minutes or until crispy. 
Finely chop the herbs, garlic and chilli. Add the oil and vinegar 3:1 ratio and season to taste. 
Remove potatoes from the oven and enjoy with copious amounts of chimichurri. 

Enjoy!

✨COLLAGEN CHALLENGE...

Collagen is a protein found in muscles, tendons, skin, ligaments, and bones. It makes up about 30% to 40% of proteins in the human body.  As we get older our bodies make less of it and lower quality collagen. Skin becomes thinner and sags while ligaments lose their elasticity, joints get stiffer and much more. 

As our bodies begin to lose collagen from 30 it’s essential we make sure we are getting enough collagen. The effects become noticeable after several years. Even though this is a natural process, it’s possible to accelerate & slow down collagen loss. 

The below can interupt and reduce natural collagen production: 
🍔 Consuming too much sugary food and refined carbs 
🚬 Smoking 
☀️ Exposure to UV rays 
💦 Pollution

As the amount of collagen decreases, other parts of your body suffer as well:
👉 Bones – become weaker and more fragile
👉 Joints – cartilage wears out, causing pain & making it tough to stay active
👉 Muscles – function decreases affecting mobility and balance

Collagen can be found in many foods and also supplements! I love @vitalproteins.uk 

Foods such as:
🍣Fish with skin on
🍗Chicken bones 
🍳Egg whites 
🍋Fruits and veg, such as citrus fruits, berries, tropical fruits, leafy greens, peppers and tomatoes

How do you make sure you're getting enough collagen?

 Easy coconut chickpea curry 
.
Get the recipe below by @happyskinkitchen : 
Recipe: 1 can of chickpeas
1/2 can of coconut milk 
1/2 can of chopped tomatoes 
1 onion – finely chopped 
2-3 garlic cloves – minced 
1 tsp of turmeric powder 
1/2 tsp of chilli powder
1 tsp of curry powder 
Salt to taste 
To serve: rice and veggies of your choice

Add a dash of oil to a large pan and once hot add in the chopped onion. Fry the onion gently for 3-4 minutes until it starts to caramelised. Add in all the spices + the garlic cloves. Cook for another minute and continue stirring to avoid burning. Add a dash of water to prevent from sticking. Add in the drained chickpeas, coconut milk and tinned tomatoes. Mix everything together, add bit of boiling water just to enough to cover the chickpeas. Put the lid on an cook on a low heat for 20-25 minutes. Serve with some rice and veggies.

Last nights dinner - another one of my absolute favourites🤤 chicken & chorizo jambalaya😍

Ingredients (serves 4)-
1/2 white onion 
1/2 red pepper 
1/2 yellow pepper 
1 & 1/2 chicken breast diced
75g chorizo 
1 chopped tinned tomatoes 
2 crushed garlics 
200g long grain rice 
1 tbsp Cajun seasoning 
350ml chicken stock 
Salt and pepper to season 

Start by frying the onions, peppers and garlic with a tbsp of olive oil until soft. Then add your diced chicken and Cajun seasoning and cook until browned. Once chicken is brown add in your chorizo and cook for 2-3 minutes. Next you add in the rice, tomatoes and chicken stock, cover and simmer for 25-30minutes until rice is tender.

Papaya for snack

#healthyrecipes #healtylifestyle

🍚 This rice hack will CHANGE your LIFE.

Post by @foodess

Instead of precisely measuring your rice and water and hoping for the best, simply fill a large pot with water as you would for pasta.

Add rice and cook at a low boil until soft. Strain for a couple of minutes in a colander. You'll get fluffy, separate grains - or in other words, perfect rice, every time!

WHAT TO COOK - literally ANY GRAIN, not just rice. Quinoa, barley, amaranth, millet - you name it, it can be done this way. WHY have we been making our lives more difficult all this time?

HOW LONG TO COOK - it depends on the rice/grain variety. Start testing doneness about 5 minutes sooner than it takes making it according to package instructions (my white basmati takes about 15 minutes).

HOW MUCH SALT - add 2 tsp kosher salt per litre/quart of water for perfectly-seasoned rice (or pasta, potatoes, etc.), or use half that amount if you prefer barely-seasoned grains as a blank canvas.

Strawberry cheesecake for breakfast 🍓🍰

Call it dessert, call it breakfast, call it whatever you want. All that really matters is, is it delicious? 
And yes WILDHONEY’S can confirm its mouth-watering goodness 🤤

The deets: 
-50g all bran ( @kelloggs_za )
-34g protein powder ( @goldsgymnutritionsa )
-100ml unsweetened almond milk (@almondbreezesa )
-150g yogurt 
-70g strawberries (cut in small pieces) 
-20g cottage cheese ( @lancewood.co.za )
-3g crunch granola ( @futurelifeza )

Instructions: 
The base : 
Mix together all-bran, almond milk, 1/2 of the yogurt, 30g protein powder and strawberries to create your base.

Cheesecake layer: 
Mix together cottage cheese, the rest of the yogurt, 4g protein powder to create a creamy texture. 
Spread over the all-bran base. 

Topping: 
Top off with some strawberries and sprinkle crunch granola for some crunchiness.

This week we are continuing on with another delicious and also healthy Mexican meal plan with our Chicken Tacos, Pico de Gallo and a crunchy and colourful Mexican Bean Salad.⁠
⁠
Click the link in our bio @granluchito or see below for recipe.⁠
⁠
Ingredients - ⁠
Chicken:⁠
500g /1.1 lbs of chicken breasts⁠
2 teaspoons Gran Luchito Smoky Chipotle Fajita and Taco Mix⁠
1 lime (juice)⁠
2 tablespoons olive oil⁠
Salt and freshly ground black pepper (for seasoning)⁠
⁠
Guacamole:⁠
2 ripe avocados⁠
½ red onion (finely diced)⁠
1 jalapeño (finely chopped)⁠
1 tablespoon extra virgin olive oil⁠
⁠
Pico de Gallo:⁠
2 vine tomatoes (diced)⁠
½ red onion (finely diced)⁠
1 tablespoon extra virgin olive oil⁠
1 lime (juice)⁠
1 handful of coriander (roughly chopped)⁠
⁠
To Serve:⁠
6 Gran Luchito Soft Tacos Wraps⁠
⁠
How to make it - ⁠
1. Add the Smoky Chipotle Fajita and Taco Mix onto your chicken breasts with the lime juice, 1 tablespoon of olive oil, a pinch of salt and freshly ground black pepper. Cover with cling film and let it marinate for 20 mins at least.⁠
2. In the meantime prepare a quick guacamole. Add the avocado flesh into a bowl and mash it with a fork. Add the onion, jalapeno, extra virgin olive oil, a pinch of salt and black pepper, then mix and set aside.⁠
3. In a different bowl prepare a quick pico de gallo. Mix the tomatoes, onion, extra virgin olive oil, lime juice, coriander, salt and pepper.⁠
4. Get the barbecue going or heat up a cast-iron skillet with the remaining olive oil. Grill or pan-fry your marinated chicken and let it get a bit of colour on both sides. Finish cooking it covered with a lid, to allow it to cook fully without getting dry.⁠
5. Once ready, remove from the heat and cut the chicken into strips with a sharp knife. Serve your chicken with warm Soft Taco Wraps, a good amount of guacamole and some of the pico de gallo. Finally don’t forget to try some Gran Luchito Salsas!

Hallöchen ihr Lieben,

ich hoffe ihr seid entspannt in die neue Woche gestartet. Ich habe zurzeit Urlaub und dachte ich stelle mich direkt mal wieder in die Küche und tüftelt an neuen Rezepten. Das Resultat sind Bounty-Brownie-Schnitten, die mir selbst meine Eltern, die dem zuckerfreien Backen eher skeptisch gegenüber stehen, aus der Hand gerissen haben. Für mich ein eindeutiges Indiz, das Rezept mit euch zu teilen. 😅

Ihr benötigt folgende Zutaten: 

Boden: 
50g Dinkelmehl 
20g Proteinpulver Schoko (oder mehr Mehl) 
30g Backkakao 
60ml (Hafer-) Milch
200g Skyr
1 Ei 
5g Flavourpowder Kokos o. Schoko
(wer es süßer mag, kann 2g mehr nehmen)

Für den Belag: 
65g Weichweizengrieß
400ml (Hafer-)Milch 
50g Kokosraspeln 
5g Flavourpowder Kokos 

Topping: 
40g dunkle Schokolade (am besten zuckerfreie) 

Zubereitung: 
1️⃣ Backofen auf 180 Grad Ober/Unterhitze vorheizen. 
2️⃣ Alle Zutaten für den Boden in eine Schüssel geben und zu einem leicht zähen, klebrigen Brownieteig verrühren und in einer kleinen Brownie-/Kastenform verteilen. 
3️⃣ Die Milch für den Belag in einen Topf geben und zum Kochen bringen. 
4️⃣ In der Zwischenzeit den Grieß mit dem Flavourpowder vermengen und bei mittlerer Hitze in die kochende Milch einrühren. 
5️⃣ Wenn der Grießbrei etwas abgekühlt ist, könnt ihr zum Schluss die Kokosraspeln unterheben und die Masse auf dem Brownieteig verteilen. 
6️⃣ Für ca. 30 min backen und anschließend gut auskühlen lassen. 
7️⃣ Brownies nun in 8 gleich große Schnitten schneiden. 
8️⃣ Schokolade über einem Wasserbad schmelzen und gleichmäßig auf den Brownies verteilen. 
9️⃣ Für mindestens 1-2 std in den Kühlschrank, bis die Schokolade fest und knackig geworden ist. 

Nährwerte/Brownie 
Ca.150 

Viel Spaß beim Ausprobieren. 😊

المواظبة علي شرب المياه مش عشان خاطر الكلي بس 😂❤️
جسمك كله بيتأثر بقلة المياه و بشرتك و شعرك و خلايا الجسم بوجه العموم🚶‍♂️
الاملاح و الفيتامينات و المعادن الجسم بيتخلص منها عن طريق البول 
و قلة كمية المياه اللي بتستخدم في التخلص من البول لما بتكون قليلة بيعلي تركيز العناصر دي كلها 
و بتتكون "كريستالات" اللي هي بالبلدي حصاوي الكلي و حصاوي مجري البول

بتكون مؤلمة جدا و بتسد مجري البول و احيانا بتحتاج تدخل جراحي عشان المشكلة تتحل💔

علي حسب الاكاديمية الوطنية للعلوم في الولايات المتحدة الاميركية حددت ان الكمية من fluid intake (يعني المدخول اليومي للسوائل) 
المفروض تستهلك خلال اليوم حوالي 15.5 كوب يوميا لرجل بالغ يعني حوالي 3.7 لتر ، و 11.5 كوب يوميا لإمرأة بالغة يعني حوالي 2.7 لتر يوميا 
مش شرط يكونوا كلهم مياه صافية المشروبات كمان بتتحسب💪🏻🔥

INGREDIENTS ⬇️⬇️⬇️
1.5 lb. boneless, skinless chicken breasts, cut into 2-inch pieces
1 Tbsp olive oil, or avocado oil
1 tsp dried oregano
1 tsp dried thyme
1 tsp cayenne
sea salt and fresh ground black pepper to taste, about 1/4 teaspoon each

For the Tzatziki dip:
1 cup plain whole Greek yogurt
1/2 cup seeded, grated cucumber
3 Tbsps chopped fresh dill
2 Tbsps fresh lemon juice
3 fresh garlic cloves, minced
sea salt and fresh ground black pepper to taste

INSTRUCTIONS ⬇️⬇️⬇️
Start by making your Tzatziki dip: combine all ingredients in a bowl/jar, taste test, adjust as desired, then refrigerate until ready to use.

If using wooden skewers, allow them to begin soaking in water for at least 20 minutes, to prevent burning.

Next, preheat your grill to medium-high.

In a medium bowl, add your chicken pieces and sprinkle with oregano, thyme, cayenne, sea salt and pepper, then drizzle with oil, and toss and stir well to coat.

Thread 2-3 pieces of chicken onto each skewer, then arrange them on the grill with some space in between each skewer.

Close the grill lid and cook for about 7 minutes until chicken is cooked through, flipping them a couple of times during cooking time.

Serve skewers with Tzatziki dip, lemon wedges, and your favorite fresh chopped veggies!.

𝐑𝐞𝐳𝐞𝐩𝐭: 𝐠𝐞𝐠𝐫𝐢𝐥𝐥𝐭𝐞 𝐇𝐨𝐧𝐢𝐠𝐟𝐫ü𝐜𝐡𝐭𝐞 🧡
.
Gegrillte Früchte bieten dir eine großartige Ergänzung zu den herzhaften Grillzutaten und können super als Nachtisch verwendet werden.
.
𝐙𝐮𝐭𝐚𝐭𝐞𝐧 𝐟ü𝐫 𝟒 𝐏𝐨𝐫𝐭𝐢𝐨𝐧𝐞𝐧:
🍍 1/2 Ananas
🍓 200 g Erdbeeren
🍑 2 Pfirsiche
🍌 2 Bananen
🍊 50 ml Orangensaft
🍯 2 EL Honig
🧡 4 EL Orangenlikör
🥥 gehackte Pistazienkerne oder Kokosraspel zum Bestreuen
.
.
𝐙𝐮𝐛𝐞𝐫𝐞𝐢𝐭𝐮𝐧𝐠:
1️⃣ Ananas schälen, in Spalten schneiden, holzigen Kern entfernen. Ananas in Scheiben schneiden. Erdbeeren waschen, putzen und je nach Größe eventuell halbieren. Pfirsiche waschen, entsteinen und in Spalten schneiden. Die Bananen schälen und in Stücke schneiden. 
.
2️⃣ Ananas und Pfirsiche auf einer Grillschale unter Wenden circa 6 bis 8 Minuten grillen. Mehrmals mit Orangensaft einpinseln. Nach 4 Minuten Erdbeeren und Bananen dazugeben. 
.
3️⃣ Honig und Likör verrühren. Früchte auf Tellern anrichten, mit Honig-Likör-Mischung beträufeln und mit Pistazien bestreuen. Schmeckt besonders gut zu Zitronensorbet. 
.
.

Für 8 Riegel:

1 EL Chiasamen in

75g zarte Haferflocken mit
35g gemahlenen Haselnüssen
1/4 TL Zimt
1/4 TL Backpulver 
1/4 TL Natron
20g Kokosöl
25g Zuckerrübensirup
10g Leinsamen
15g Sonnenblumenkerne
35g gemischte, gehackte Nüsse 
15g Rosinen und den Chiasamen vermengen, in die Riegel-Form (habe ich mal bei Tchibo gekauft) füllen und für 20-25 Min. bei 160 Grad Umluft im vorgeheizten Backofen backen. Auf einem Rost auskühlen lassen und in einer Keksdose aufbewahren 😉!

INGREDIENTS
.
Olive oil 1 TBS
Onion chopped 70 g/2.5 oz
Ground beef 450 g/1 Lb/16 oz
Green or yellow pepper chopped 80 g/2.8 oz
Red pepper chopped 145 g/5.12 oz
Minced garlic 3 cloves
Canned crushed tomato 1 cup/200 ml
Beef broth 1.5 cup/300 ml
Water 2 cups/400 ml
Salt ½ teaspoon or more to taste
Pepper to taste
Ground paprika 1 tsp
Turmeric 1 tsp
Dried basil 1 tsp
Dried oregano 1 tsp
Freshly chopped parsley 1 TBS
FOR SERVING
Sour cream
Freshly chopped parsley
Spring onion chopped
Shredded cheddar cheese

INSTRUCTIONS
.
In a large pot, heat 1 TBS of olive oil.
When olive oil is hot, add chopped onion and stir until onion is golden brown and caramelized.
When onion is caramelized, add ground beef and stir occasionally until it's brown and caramelized.
Add chopped pepper and minced garlic, stir for few minutes until garlic release all the oils, smell and flavor.
Add crushed tomato, broth and water, salt, pepper and spices (everything except fresh parsley).
Stir and bring it to boil. When starts boiling, cook covered for 20 minutes on medium heat.
After 20 minutes try and add more salt if needed, cook uncovered for 5 to 10 minutes more and add chopped fresh parsley.
.
.

👶 Baby Friendly👶

Ingrediente:

☆100g unt cu 65% grăsime @lidlromania
☆30g smântână cu 30% grasime @lidlromania
☆100g făină albă tip 650
☆100g făină de secară @sano_vita
☆1 ou
☆1 linguriță praf de copt bio @biomarketro 
☆1 linguriță esență de vanilie @droetker_ro 
☆1 lingură sirop de cocos @biomarketro 
☆gem de prune fără zahăr @niavis.ro 
☆brânză de vaci @lidlromania 
☆mascarpone @lidlromania 
☆zmeură @piataobor.bucuresti

Mod de preparare:

☆Se lasă untul la temperatura camereu ca să se înmoaie și apoi îl mixăm impreună cu smântâna, siropul de cocos și oul
☆Adăugăm apoi, făina, praful de copt, vanilia și mai mixăm puțin
☆Frământăm puțin aluatul cu mâna și apoi îl punem în folie alimentară și îl lăsăm la frigider în jur de 30 de minute
☆Scoatem aluatul, îl împărțim în mai multe bucăți și începem să întindem cu ajutorul unui făcăleț fiecare bucată
☆Tăiem aluatul în trigunghiuri și umplem cu gem sau cremă de brânză, mascarpone și zmeură (le amestecăm înainte pe cele 3 ingrediente pentru a obține o cremă)
☆Când am format toate cornulețele, le punem într-o tavă pe folie de copt și le dăm la cuptor, la 180 de grade, până când se rumenesc deasupra

○ Se servesc alături de o băutură calda, lapte, chefir sau sana
○ Sunt foarte bune și pentru adulți (dacă doriți puteți umple câteva cornulețe și cu nutella)

PANCAKE KAMUT-OKARA

Ho inventato questa ricettina con gli ingredienti che avevo sotto mano.. della farina di kamut rimasta e l'okara di nocciole del latte che avevo fatto qualche giorno fa.
Provatela! E ditemi che ne pensate! 😊

INGREDIENTI

🌴100g di farina di kamut
🌴60g di Okara di nocciole (vedi latte vegetale nelle storie in evidenza)
🌴10g amido di mais 🌽
🌴1 cucchiaino di bicarbonato 
🌴1 Pizzico di sale 🧂
🌴1 cucchiaio 🥄 di miele di castagno bio 🍯 
🌴170ml di latte di nocciole fatto in casa 🍶 (vedi latte vegetale nelle storie in evidenza)
🌴2 #uovabio 🥚

GUARNIZIONE

🌴 Sciroppo d'acero bio
🌴Frutta di stagione (io dei mirtilli e pesche noci)

PROCEDIMENTO

🔆Ho unito gli ingredienti solidi in una ciotola e mescolato con la frusta.
🔆In una ciotola a parte ho montato con le fruste elettriche le uova con il cucchiaio di miele.
🔆Ho versato la spuma uova-miele nel composto e mescolato con delicatezza dall'alto verso il basso.
🔆 Ho scaldato scaldato un padellino con un filino d'olio evo e tamponato con della carta assorbente e versato un ramaiolo di pastella. Formatosi i forellini ho girato dall'altro lato. E così via col restante della pastella.

Petits pains au lait chocolat🍫

Pour 14 petits pains:
-400gr de farine
-100gr de chocolat
-25cl de lait
-60gr de fromage blanc
-2oeufs 
-1CaS de miel
-1sachet de levure boulangère

✳Melange farine+levure+chocolat
✴Fais un puit et ajoute le fromage blanc, le lait, les oeufs et le miel
✴Pétris la pâte, et laisses poser sous un torchon 2h30
✴Dégaze la pâte et forme les boules, dispose sur une plaque allant au four et laisse denouveau poser 1h30
✴Badigeonne de lait et fais cuir 15-20min a 180°C

Total pour un pain 153kcal

Rashladite se uz jednostavne RAWBITE proteinske sladolede koji su gotovi za svega 5 minuta! 😉

Za izradu 4 sladoleda potrebno vam je:
✔️1 avokado
✔️2 velike banane
✔️2 dl kokosove vode
✔️2 Rawbite protein pločice
✔️korica jedne limete

1.Stavite jednu Rawbite pločicu u blender ili u multipraktik i miksajte dok ne dobijete mrvičastu smjesu. Stavite smjesu u zdjelu.
2. Zajedno s ostalim sastojcima stavite drugu RAWBITE pločicu u blender i ponovno izmiksajte. Smoothie treba biti dovoljno tekuć da se može preliti. Ako nije dovoljno tekuće, dodajte još kokosove vode.
3. Ulijte smoothie u 4 kalupa za sladoled i pospite ih mrvicama od prve Rawbite pločice.
4. Zamrznite najmanje 4 sata prije uživanja u proteinskim sladoledima RAWBITE!

Mettez du Tofu dans vos assiettes ! Cet été on vous dit tout sur la préparation du Tofu pour faire l'unanimité autour de vos tablées estivales.

Cette semaine on commence par une préparation bien connue des habitués de la cuisine végétale : LE TOFU MARINÉ !

Le Tofu cuisiné en marinade est apprécié pour sa diversité de saveurs car il y a autant de recettes de marinades que d'adeptes de Tofu ! 😋

Et pour une marinade réussie et se régaler à tous les coups, voici nos conseils :

👉 Avant tout, éponger votre Tofu pour enlever l'excédent d'eau
👉 Piquer votre Tofu avec la pointe d'un couteau pour faciliter la pénétration de la marinade
👉 Anticiper : plus votre Tofu repose dans la marinade, plus le goût sera intense. Cependant si vous êtes pressé 15 à 20 minutes suffisent pour parfumer le Tofu.
👉 Prévoyez un récipient à couvercle pour pouvoir refermer la préparation pendant le temps de repos

Le Tofu peut être découpé en dés, en bâtonnets, en tranches ou encore émietté pour être ajouté à votre préparation.

ℹ️ Toutes ces astuces sont valables pour tous nos types de tofus : natures, fumés et aromatisés.

Dites-nous si cela vous a été utile en commentaire ! 👇💬

Are you planning a party or just a get together with some friends?
These Mestemacher HAM-MELON-LEMON BUTTER CANAPÉS will surely do the trick when it comes to your canape table!
 
For 12 pieces
 
100g butter
1 teaspoon of lemon juice
salt, pepper
Mestemacher protein bread – cut out in a round form or quarter
¼ cantaloupe melon
12 slices of raw ham
red pepper
12 wooden skewers
 
Mix the butter with lemon juice, salt, and pepper. Spread the protein bread with it. Cut the melon in pieces or cut out balls with a melon baller. Put a piece of melon and slice of ham on each piece of bread with a wooden skewer. Garnish with red bell pepper.

CURRIED VEGGIE NOODLES 🍜 🌱 another high protein vegan meal ~ takes about 10 minutes to whip up + is super filling. And delicious of course!!
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
Weekday lunches/dinners at their very finest 🤌🏼
✅Over 30g protein per serve too!
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
I know the cauliflower chips on top is super random but I had them in the cupboard and I love some crunch on a stir fry, so this worked perfectly!!😆🤗
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
RECIPE (makes 2 serves):
100-150g @nooeynoods lupin fettuccine, or edamame noodles
1 carrot, diced 
1/2 onion, diced
1 cup broccoli, diced 
2 cloves of garlic, thinly sliced 
1 cup kale, chopped 
3 mushrooms, sliced 
2 tsp curry paste
1 tsp curry powder 
1 tbsp soy sauce or tamari 
2 tbsp sweet chilli sauce
Juice 1/2 lemon
Handful of curry cauliflower chips, to serve 
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
1️⃣Heat a pan with a lil sesame oil, then stir fry carrot, broccoli, onion, garlic + mushroom until just soft.
2️⃣Cook noodles according to packet directions.
3️⃣Add curry paste, curry powder, soy sauce, sweet chilli, lemon, kale and noodles to pan. Keep cooking until kale is wilted.
4️⃣Serve topped cauliflower chips!
ENJOY 💛💛

Нещо тропическо, свежо и идеално за лятото.
Тази диетична протеинова бленда съдържа много полезни съставки, а именно:
✨Глюкоманан-диетични фибри
✨Витамин B5
✨Смес от ензими, които спомагат за по-бързото разбиване на протеина до аминокиселини

✨CLA powder - естествено срещаща се мастна киселина от шафраново масло

Perfekt als leckerer Energieschub am Morgen oder für zwischendurch.
Ich hab mir heut den leckeren Bananen-Kaffee-Smoothie als Energiekick für zwischendurch auf Arbeit gemacht.

Durch die Banane und den Kakao stillt er perfekt die Lust auf Süßes und der Kaffee liefert die Energie.
Der Bananen-Kaffee-Smoothie hat nur winzige 122kcal und passt somit immer rein 🤗

Die Zutaten für 2 Portionen findet ihr wenn ihr nach rechts swiped ➡️
Die Zubereitung ist wieder ganz schnell und einfach 😊:
Zuerst die Haferflocken mit dem Mixer(ich mach alles mit dem Smoothiemaker) zu Mehl mahlen, dann Kakao und Zimt dazu geben und noch eine Runde drehen lassen, dass sich die trockenen Zutaten miteinander vermischen.
Dann die restlichen Zutaten hinzugeben (Kaffee kalt) und im Smoothiemaker mixen.

Entweder sofort genießen oder bis zum Genuss kühl stellen 😊

Ό,τι πιο δροσερό και καλοκαιρινό μπορείτε να απολαύσετε τα απογεύματα σας!
Σας το δείχνω με πολύ αγάπη και εύχομαι σε όλους καλή απόλαυση💜

Υλικα:
-170 γρ. γιουρτακι με γεύση φράουλα( εγώ έβαλα το super spoon φράουλα)*
-30 γρ. Philadelphia light
-Λίγα κατεψυγμένα κκοκκινα φρουτα
-ένα κουταλάκι μέλι 
-Ένα μπισκότο πτι Μπερ
-stevia drops(προαιρετικά)
-20γρ λευκη σοκολατα.
-2-3 αμυγδαλα σπασμένα (προαιρετικά)
*αν δε θέλετε γιαουρτάκι φράουλα βάλτε απλό στραγγιστό, απλά θα γίνει λιγότερο φραουλενιο!

✅Βάζουμε τα φρούτα σε ένα κατσαρολάκι με το μέλι και τα πατάμε να χάσουν τα υγρά τους και να μείνει μόνο η μαρμελάδα.
Αν το θέλουμε πιο γλυκό προσθέτουμε ένα κουταλάκι μέλι ακόμα.
✅Ανακατεύουμε το γιαουρτάκι με το Φιλαδέλφεια και αν θέλουμε 2-3 στέβια drops.
✅Προσθέτουμε ένα σπασμένο μπισκότο και τησάλτσα που φτιάξαμε!
✅ Ανακατεύουμε ελαφρά γιατί θέλουμε η σάλτσα να μείνει ακέραιη  σε ορισμένα μέρη!
✅Βάζουμε για λίγο στην κατάψυξη.
✅Λιώνουμε την λευκή σοκολάτα με μισό κουταλάκι λάδι Καρύδας και περιχύνουμε το cheesecake μας!
✅Αν θέλουμε ρίχνουμε από πάνω λίγα σπασμένα αμύγδαλα και βάζουμε και πάλι στο στην κατάψυξη αν βιαζόμαστε ή στο ψυγείο για μια ωρα τουλάχιστον!

CHOCOLATE BAKED OATS 😋 I love chocolate and I love cake - they’re the two things that in the past would usually let me down when I tried to follow a healthy eating regime. Thanks to all the inspiration here I’m finding ways to still have my cake and eat it (lol!) while not undoing my hard work. I baked this last night to eat this morning and it was yummy! It works out as 4 syns and 320 calories per portion. Recipe below - I made this for me and my husband, so just half the ingredients if it’s just for one person🔻

Ingredients:
16 Aero chocolate melts - 8 melts per person at 1/2 syn per melt (4 syns per portion)
80g oats (40g = 1 HEXb)
60ml semi skimmed milk (1/4 HEXa)
1/3 cup zero calorie sweetener (free)
2 eggs (free)
2 tsp vanilla essence (free)
1 tsp baking powder 

1. Preheat your oven at gas mark 5/6 or 180 degrees Celsius. Grease a baking dish with cooking spray.
2. Blitz your oats in a food processor and then mix into a bowl with 1/3 cup sweetener and 1 tsp baking powder.
3. Crack 2 eggs into the bowl and mix thoroughly.
4. Add 2 tsp vanilla essence and 60ml of semi skimmed milk and stir the batter again.
5. Fold in 16 Aero melts - 8 melts per portion is 4 syns.
6. Pop into the oven for half an hour or until a toothpick inserted comes out clean. Leave to cool before eating!

BLUEBERRY COCONUT OATS 🥥🫐 (English below 👇🏻)

🇩🇪Heute wieder ein leckeres Porridge Rezept für euch. 🥥🫐 Heidelbeeren kombiniert mit Kokos Geschmack, so startet es sich gut in den Dienstag oder?

2 Portionen ➡️

- 90g Haferflocken 
- 20g Kokosnuss Protein
- 5g Chia Samen
- 150-200ml Kokosdrink
- Süße nach Wahl (z.B. Kokosblütenzucker
- 60g gefrorene Heidelbeeren 

Toppings: Heidelbeeren, Himbeeren, Papaya, Pfirsich, Nussmus 

Zubereitung ➡️

Alles bis auf die gefrorenen Beeren und Toppings im Topf bei mittlerer Hitze circa 10min cremig kochen. Heidelbeeren unterheben und weitere 3min köcheln. Auf Schüsseln verteilen, toppen und schmecken lassen. 😊

BLUEBERRY COCONUT OATS 🥥 🫐

🇬🇧Today another delicious porridge recipe for you. 🥥  Blueberries combined with coconut flavor, that's a good way to start Tuesday, right?

2 Portions ➡️

- 90g oats
- 20g coconut protein
- 5g of chia seeds
- 150-200ml coconut drink
- Sweetener of your choice (e.g. coconut blossom sugar
- 60g frozen blueberries

Toppings: blueberries, raspberries, papaya, peach, nut butter

Preparation ➡️

Cook everything except the frozen berries and toppings in a saucepan over medium heat for about 10 minutes until creamy. Fold in the blueberries and simmer for another 3 minutes. Pour into bowls, top and enjoy. 😊

You're one decision away from getting back on track 👏⁠
⁠
If you haven’t been able to stay on track today.. or this week didn't start off going to plan…⁠
⁠
Remember, YOU are the only one who can make the decision to get back on track 🤗⁠
⁠
That doesn't mean suddenly doing every single habit you were doing when things were going well.⁠
⁠
“Getting back on track” means doing ONE small thing to demonstrate to yourself that you take your fitness goals seriously.⁠
⁠
⚡️Go for a 20 minute walk.⁠
⚡️Drink a glass of water.⁠
⚡️Go to bed 10 minutes earlier than usual.⁠
⚡️Prepare tomorrow's lunch.⁠
⁠
It doesn’t matter WHAT it is.⁠
⁠
It just matters that you do SOMETHING 🙌⁠
⁠
MAKE yourself take this small action. Get the ball rolling, and you’ll be back to your habits before you know it! 💪⁠

Start the week with an easy, healthy, and tasty snack! 🙌Raw food cacao balls! 

What you’ll need: 
✅ 1/2 cup walnuts⁠
✅ 5Medjooll dates pitted⁠
✅ 3 tablespoons KIKI Health Raw Organic Cacao Powder ( link in bio) 
✅ 1 tablespoon finely chopped walnuts

How you'll make it: 
👉 Blend ½ cup walnuts, dates, and cacao powder together in a blender until almost smooth
👉 Roll mixture into little balls. 

👉 Place finely chopped walnuts in a shallow bowl and roll balls in walnuts to coat.

How sustainable can bamboo be? 

Say hello to our bamboo cutlery and wish goodbye to the plastic ones! ✨

Bamboo is a sustainable material because it grows so quickly. It grows about 2 feet per day.

Bamboo cutlery is one of the best ways you can implement sustainable food practice. It can help reduce waste and is made of durable material. Most especially, it is compostable and lightweight, which makes it ideal for takeaway restaurants. 

At Verdantli, it is our goal to encourage you to practice sustainability and give you products that could make you sustainable. ☘️

Benefits of bamboo cutlery: 
🌱Supply is not likely to run out for it is a fast growing plant.
🌱It is safe because it contains an antibacterial and antimicrobial properties.
🌱It can be reused for 5-6 months.

Mention a friend and be part of the change! 🌳🌍

Good food is good mood 🍔 Gezond, makkelijk, maar lekker eten! Dat is wat je wil toch?! 🤩 Probeer eens deze groenteburger met ovengroente. 🫑

Wat heb je nodig voor 2 personen? 
- zak van 600 gram ovengroente 
- 2 ongepaneerde groenteburgers 
- 2 volkoren bollen 
- 1 eetlepel olijfolie 
- optioneel: 1 eetlepel YoFresh en 1 eetlepel mosterd 

Hoe te maken? 
- verwarm de oven voor op 220 graden en bak hierin vervolgens de groente 30-40 minuten gaar
- bak ondertussen in een beetje olijfolie de groenteburger mooi bruin 
- snijd de volkoren bollen en besmeer met een dun laagje YoFresh en mosterd en leg hier boven op de burger 
- serveer daarnaast de groenten uit de oven 

Simpel maar oooh zo lekker! 🤤 en maar 550 kcal!😍👏🏼

YUM 😋

[RECIPE]

SALTED CARAMEL CRUNCH SLICE🍫​​​​​​​​
​​​​​​​​
BASE ​​​​​​​​
1 & 2/3 cups almond meal​​​​​​​​
2/3 cup desiccated coconut​​​​​​​​
2 heaped tbsp coconut oil​​​​​​​​
2 tbsp pure maple syrup​​​​​​​​
​​​​​​​​
CARAMEL​​​​​​​​
250g cashew butter​​​​​​​​
1 cup pure maple syrup​​​​​​​​
1 tsp vanilla​​​​​​​​
Salt flakes, to taste​​​​​​​​
​​​​​​​​
TOPPING​​​​​​​​
1 cup roasted skinned hazelnuts OR mixed nuts250g 70-80% organic dark chocolate OR homemade Naked chocolate, melted. ​​​​​​​​
​​​​​​​​
METHOD​​​​​​​​
1. Process all base ingredients until well combined and sticks together. Line a square container with baking paper. Press base in firmly, set aside in the freezer.​​​​​​​​
2. Blend all caramel ingredients together until smooth. Spread over base. Scatter nuts over the slice and press into the caramel gently.​​​​​​​​
3. Pour over melted chocolate. Set in the freezer.​​​​​​​​
​​​​​​​​
Slice and enjoy!

Most health bars have the same or more sugar than a big chocolate chip cookie! ⁠
⁠
I'm not trying to make you feel bad, it isn't easy because these health bars look so wholesome but in reality most of them are high in sugars which means:⁠
⁠
💫 You'll likely be hungry again soon after eating 💫⁠
💫 Your body stores high blood sugar in the fat cells 💫⁠
💫 Your cortisol can be spiked from the high sugar 💫⁠
⁠
If you are buying health bars, aim for ones that have less than 5g of sugar per serving, it'll be more gentle on your blood sugar in the long run. ⁠

Keto Broccoli Salad

100% effective keto diet program LINK IN BIO @keto_recipes_every_day

INGREDIENTS
FOR THE SALAD
Kosher salt
3 heads broccoli, cut into bite-size pieces
1/2 c. cheddar, shredded
1/4 red onion, thinly sliced
1/4 c. toasted sliced almonds
3 slices bacon, cooked and crumbled
2 tbsp. freshly chopped chives 
FOR THE DRESSING
2/3 c. mayonnaise
3 tbsp. apple cider vinegar
1 tbsp. dijon mustard
Kosher salt
Freshly ground black pepper

If you don't know how to start ketodiet properly or do you want to lose possibly 5-10 lbs in the first week alone with keto Join "Custom Keto Diet". LINK IN BIO @keto_recipes_every_day

DIRECTIONS
In a medium pot or saucepan, bring 6 cups of salted water to a boil. While waiting for the water to boil, prepare a large bowl with ice water.
Add broccoli florets to the boiling water and cook until tender, 1 minute. Remove with a slotted spoon and  immediately place in the prepared bowl of ice water. When cool, spin the broccoli in a salad spinner. You will need to spin it at least twice.
In a medium bowl, whisk to combine dressing ingredients. Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Combine all salad ingredients in a large bowl and pour over dressing. Toss until ingredients are combined and fully coated in dressing. Refrigerate until ready to serve.

NEW RECIPE: Lemon & Poppyseed Cake 

Coming at you with another lemon recipe for all you zesty lemon lovers 🍋 

INGREDIENTS/ METHOD 
(Preheat oven to 180 degrees and line/ spray cake tin) 
1.5 cups almond meal 
1 cup coconut flour 
1 tsp baking powder 
1/2 tsp baking soda 
1/2 tsp salt 

MIX all the dry ingredients together then add; 
3 whisked eggs 
120g melted olivani 
1/3 cup runny honey 
1/2 cup milk of choice 
1tsp vanilla essence 
3/4 cup lemon juice 
Zest of 1 lemon 
1 tbsp poppy seeds 

MIX till combined 
Cook for 45 mins/ till golden brown and bounces back to touch 

ICING: 
1.5 cups icing sugar
2 Tbsp milk of choice 
1 Tbsp lemon juice 
WHISK together and ice

Looking for a fast recipe to make for lunch? This dish is light and can be made in only 25 minutes!

✨Bok Choy with Tamari Sauce✨

Ingredients:
✅2 lb bok choy, small 
✅1 Tbs ginger, fresh, minced
✅ 1/4 cup scallions, thinly sliced 
✅1 1/2 Tbs olive oil, divided ✅6 Tbs tamari sauce 
✅1 Tbs hemp seeds 

Directions:
Prep : 
1. Trim bok choy bottoms and cut in half lengthwise. 
2. Mince ginger. 
3. Slice scallions. 

Make :
1. Coat bottom of pan with 1 1/2 teaspoons oil, over medium-high heat. When hot, lay bok choy in single layer, cut side down (do not overcrowd). Add 2 tablespoons water and cover about 2 minutes. 

2. Lift out of pan, drain, and place on platter. Remove water from pan and repeat with remaining bok choy. Leave residual water in pan. 

3. Add 1 tablespoon oil and ginger to pan and cook, stirring over high 
heat until ginger is browned. Remove from heat and add tamari sauce. 

4. Pour sauce over bok choy, sprinkle with scallions and hemp seeds.

Health is a factor that troubles women more than men, given that they undergo periodic menstruation and pregnancy.

Gynecological issues, for instance, have always been a focus of study when it comes to adversities faced by women. Apart from the social, cultural, and economic vulnerabilities that are further deepened due to a continuously degrading climate system, the most significant degradation that women face is that of their physical health.

What can be done? To start with, recognizing the adversity of climate change and its impact on women is important. More individuals from gender minorities should be included in the policy and decision-making processes. This will raise general awareness and meet better standards of climate adaptation policies.

This peanut butter banana smoothie recipe is DELICIOUS and it’s really simple to make! Make this quick and healthy snack in less than 5 minutes!

Ingredients
2 bananas
2 cups ice
1 cup milk
1/2 cup greek yogurt plain
2 Tablespoons peanut butter heaping
1 teaspoon vanilla extract

Instructions
Chop the bananas into smaller pieces. Or at the very least, break it in half.
Add all of the ingredients to the blender, adding the ice last.
Blend the ingredients until smooth.
Top your smoothie with melted peanut butter and/or banana pieces. (optional)
Enjoy!

*FULL RECIPE*
Here's the recipe for the Jamaican Jerk chicken with coconut rice and mango salsa that I made for dinner last night. This is a one pot recipe, so minimal cleaning up! 

JAMAICAN JERK CHICKEN WITH COCONUT RICE AND MANGO SALSA

You're going to need:
(For 3 Servings)
3 Diced Chicken Breasts
210g Rice 
2 Chopped Red Onions
1 Chopped Red Peppers
1 Diced Mango
2 tbsp Lime Juice
2 tbsp @schwartz.uk Jamaican Jerk Seasoning
1 tsp Ground Coriander
1 1/2 tsp Garlic Granules
300ml @alpro Coconut Milk
300ml Chicken Stock

1. Coat your chicken in the @schwartz.uk Jamaican Jerk seasoning and fry until fully cooked.
2. Add in 1 onion, 1 tbsp of lime juice and the garlic granules, mix well and fry for a further 5 minutes.
3. Wash your rice then add to the pan with the chicken, frying for a minute to toast it.
4. Add in the @alpro coconut milk and chicken stock, bring to the boil, reduce the heat then cover and simmer for 20-25 minutes, stirring occasionally, until the rice is cooked. 
5. Meanwhile, mix the other onion, red pepper, mango, 1 tbsp lime juice and the coriander together to form your mango salsa.
6. Once cooked, top the chicjen and rice with the salsa and enjoy!

Let me know in the comments if you try this recipe and what you think of it!

Prawn Taco Bowl

Perfect for a hot summer’s day, this is my spiced prawn bowl with lime rice and homemade guacamole. 

Shrimp spices:
90g raw king prawns 
Juice of 1/2 lime 
1/2tsp garlic powder 
1/2tsp chilli powder 
1/2tsp coriander powder 
Fry for 2 minutes until pink. 

Simple guacamole:
1/2 avocado 
1/4 red chilli, diced 
Season to taste with lime juice and salt

Lime rice: 
125g cooked long grain rice 
Seasoned with a pinch of salt, juice of 1/2 lime and 2tsp chopped coriander. 

Other ingredients:
Chopped Lettuce, sliced jalapeños, extra coriander chopped tomatoes and cucumber, cheese of choice. 

Assemble and serve.

Spiced Salmon Skewers
—————————————————————
These #airfryer Salmon skewers with a chimichurri dressing are perfect for a lighter Summer meal and so easy to make at home! 

Serves 2:
2 salmon fillets cut into cubes 
1 courgette, peeled into ribbons
1 yellow pepper, diced 
Seasoning: 1tbsp olive oil, 1tsp garlic powder, 1tsp dried oregano, 1tsp smoked paprika

Salad: 
Shredded lettuce, chopped tomatoes, cucumber, feta, sumac, lemon juice and extra virgin olive oil 

Chimichurri recipe:
Handful of fresh parsley, finely chopped
2tsp fresh oregano, chopped
1tsp dried oregano 
2 garlic cloves, finely chopped
1/2tsp dried chilli flakes
1/2 fresh red chilli, finely chopped
1/2tsp sea salt & black pepper
3tbsp extra virgin olive oil
1tbsp white wine vinegar 

Preheat airfryer to 200 degrees c. Make your skewers with the salmon, courgette ribbons and peppers and coat in the seasoning. 

Make your chimichurri and salad. 

Cook the salmon skewers for 8 minutes in the airfryer or roast them in a hot oven at 200 degrees for 12-15 minutes. 

Enjoy!

🌶️🍝🍅 CHILLI BUTTER TOMATO SPAGHETTI 🍅🍝🌶️ Long time no pasta, so just dropping by with a taste of the Med right here 🤤🤤 A fresh tomato sauce, simmered with garlic and chilli, lotttts of butter, and served with fresh pasta. So much flavour with (mostly) store cupboard ingredients, and ready in 20 - perfect for summer evenings ☀️☀️ I like mine extra saucy and extra buttery, so feel free to bump up your ingredients to suit your taste 👌🏼👌🏼

Chilli Butter Tomato Spaghetti (serves 2):

150g spaghetti
50g unsalted butter
1/2 red onion, finely chopped
350g cherry/baby plum tomatoes, halved
2 x garlic cloves, sliced
1/2 x teaspoon sea salt (may need more, adjust to taste)
1/2 x teaspoon chilli flakes
1 x tablespoon apple cider vinegar (I used @willysacv)
1/2 teaspoon sugar
Freshly cracked black pepper
Small handful parsley, chopped
50g Parmesan, grated

Cook spaghetti according to pack instructions. Save a ladle of pasta water for the sauce.

On a medium high heat, add the butter to a large saucepan and gently fry the onions for 2-3 minutes. Add the tomato halves and fry for 4-5 minutes. Add the garlic, ACV, sugar, salt, chilli, and continue to cook until the tomatoes soften and release their juices (about another 5-10 minutes). Squish the tomatoes with the back of a wooden spoon to break apart. Add enough reserved pasta water to loosen the sauce (about 50ml), the cooked spaghetti, half the parmesan and the parsley, and combine well. Season with pepper, more salt if required, and serve with the remaining parmesan on top 👌🏼👌🏼

Ingredients

4 large zucchini thinly sliced lengthwise (I used a mandoline)

1 Tbsp olive oil for brushing + 1 additional Tablespoon for sautéing

1 small sweet yellow onion, finely diced

2 fresh garlic cloves, minced

8 oz fresh mushrooms, chopped well

1 tsp dry Italian seasoning

16 ounces high quality marinara sauce

sea salt and fresh ground pepper, to taste

1/3 cup organic ricotta

1 free range egg

1/4 cup freshly grated Parmesan cheese

a handful or fresh parsley, finely chopped

1/2 cup shredded mozzarella cheese

Instructions

Preheat your oven to 375 degrees f. and line a baking tray with parchment paper.

Lay out the zucchini strips on a large cutting board, lightly sprinkle with sea salt and pepper and very lightly brush with 1 Tablespoon of oil.

Bake strips in your preheated oven for 10-12 minutes, or until slightly tender and easy to roll. Allow them to cool until ready to handle.

Meanwhile, add remaining olive oil in a skillet over medium-high heat. Add minced garlic and cook for 1 minute, until fragrant.

Add in the onions, mushrooms, Italian seasonings and cook for 4-5 minutes.

Stir in 3/4 of the marinara sauce and simmer your mushroom sauce for about 4 minutes, or until slightly reduced.

Follow me @emily_vegan_food for more vegan recipes💚

Naan is a flatbread originating from North India and it’s one of my favourite side dishes! 😋
It’s so fluffy, so, buttery and that garlic flavor hits the spot…🥰
Much love
Maya ✨
RECIPE (6 naan, 3h prep time)
-1/3 cup (90ml) plant milk, room temp
-1/8 cup (30ml) water, room temp
-1 Tsp instant yeast
-1 Tbsp sugar
-1/4 cup (60g) vegan yogurt
-2 cups (260g) flour
-1 Tsp baking powder
-a generous pinch of salt
KNEAD 5-10mins.
Let it rest 1-2h until doubled in size.
Divide into 6 pieces.
Flatten them on a floured surface.
Garlic-“butter”:
-1/4 cup (60g) vegan butter, melted
-4 minced cloves garlic
-a handful chopped parsley
Fry the naan on one’s side in a little oil.
Meanwhile spread some garlic butter on the surface.
Flip when bubbles appear.
Spread more garlic butter on the other surface.

⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
RECIPE (makes 2 serves):
100-150g @nooeynoods lupin fettuccine, or edamame noodles
1 carrot, diced 
1/2 onion, diced
1 cup broccoli, diced 
2 cloves of garlic, thinly sliced 
1 cup kale, chopped 
3 mushrooms, sliced 
2 tsp curry paste
1 tsp curry powder 
1 tbsp soy sauce or tamari 
2 tbsp sweet chilli sauce
Juice 1/2 lemon
Handful of curry cauliflower chips, to serve 
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
1️⃣Heat a pan with a lil sesame oil, then stir fry carrot, broccoli, onion, garlic + mushroom until just soft.
2️⃣Cook noodles according to packet directions.
3️⃣Add curry paste, curry powder, soy sauce, sweet chilli, lemon, kale and noodles to pan. Keep cooking until kale is wilted.
4️⃣Serve topped cauliflower chips!
ENJOY 💛💛

BRESKVA I KUPINA
Match made in heaven. 

Naravno, najljepše ih je zajedno ušuškati u galette od prhkog tijesta posutog šećerom i poslužiti uz sladoled od vanilije, ali paljenje pećnice i jedenje kolača na ovoj temperaturi mi ne pada na pamet. Doduše, ni sladoledu od vanilije s breskvama i kupinama ništa ne fali. 😊

Na fotografiji je kefir s chia sjemenkama koji sam preko noći ostavila u hladnjaku da se 'učini', a ujutro ga obilato prošarala džemom od kupina, posula cimetom i narezanim breskvama. Ukusno, osvježavajuće, zdravo, jednostavno i predivno. Ovo će mi biti podnevni obrok na poslu dok ne potrošim džem, a onda ću skuhati novi. 😀

Džem sam skuhala sama od hrpice povoljno kupljenih prezrelih kupina. Dodala sam im malo meda i polagano kuhala kako bi se raspale i zgusnule. Od dvije mjerice kupina dobila sam dvije male teglice džema, od oko 200-250 ml.

✨Yellow Thai Chicken Curry✨
 
• Ayam Yellow Thai curry paste 
• 1 can of coconut cream
• 1/2 onion & 2 cloves of garlic
• mushrooms 
• potatoes, carrots, spinach
• chicken breast 

Fry off diced onion & garlic. Add in diced chicken. Add in 2 Tblspn of curry paste. Fry this together. Then add in vegetables and cook down slightly, add in coconut cream & allow to simmer for around 20-25 mins or until veggies are soft & chicken is cooked through. 
I serve this with a bed of jasmine rice but sometimes for a change, I serve it with fettuccine or spaghetti or noodles is quite nice too.

Schezwan Chicken Pie 
mubina_18

1 and 1/2 cup shredded chicken 
1 tsp chopped garlic 
1 medium onion chopped 
1 cup thin egg noodles 
1/2 green pepper chopped 
1/2 cup spring onion chopped 
1 tbsp chili garlic sauce 
2 tbsp or more schezwan sauce 
1 tsp vinegar 
1 tsp soya sauce
1 tbsp tomato sauce 
1/2 tsp Worcestershire sauce 
Chopped coriander/ parsley 

Take oil in a pan add chopped onion n cook till soft. 
Then add chopped garlic, shredded chicken and green pepper. 
Now stir all for 2-3 min. 
Then add noodles,chili garlic sauce,schezwan sauce,tomato sauce,vinegar,soya sauce and Worcestershire sauce. 
Mix all well. 
Then lastly add chopped coriander/parsley. 
Roll puff pastry dough. 
Cut into circles n fill it then close with fork. 
Apply egg on it. 
Sprinkle some dry herbs. 
Bake @180.C till golden browns. 
Serve hot with sauce or chutney. 
Enjoy 😊

When it comes to saving and avoiding food waste, if you have quick, no fuss, flexible recipes 
(and a Thermomix)
it makes life much easier!

Fritters from leftover veggies are one of the easiest things you can make, which may have otherwise gone to waste. We ❤️ fritters 

Now there are thousands of fritter recipes to choose from. 
Corn fritters, zucchini fritters, pumpkin fritters, sweet potato fritters and the list of different types of veggie fritters goes on and on.
And of course if you have a #thermomixtm6 and #cookidoo you’ll find a stack of ideas! 

But you don’t need a recipe for each and every one of them. 
All you need is a basic fritter batter recipe, which will work with most cooked or raw veggies 

2 eggs 
1/2 a cup of flour of choice 
With 2 cups of Veggies n S&P
You can add Baking powder and some herbs (even parmo)

Serve 2 so double for more!

Roasted veggies couldn’t have tasted more delicious. No extraordinary ingredients and yet…and yet I wish I have made double to have some leftovers for lunch to take to work. Roasted aubergines with coriander and anchovy (green olive) salsa from @ixta.belfrage Mezcla 😋😋😋 More than aubergine and more than coriander to this cheerful dish of course. 
Here we have chopped aubergine, cherry tomatoes and red chillies that I happily replaced with red bell pepper (just like @teffe_kocht did), basic seasoning and lots of olive oil roasted on high for 45 minutes. Ixta warns you not to have veggies snug and for a reason. When you follow instructions the veggies turn out nice and crisp, sweet and savory, juicy enough but not soggy. Dot them with torn Buffalo mozzarella, top with garlicky, herby, lemony salsa, get your bread out and regret not having more 🙀 Haven’t I mentioned it already? For those wondering about anchovies in salsa they can be successfully substituted with green olives and this is what I did 🤩 Absolutely delicious! Mark my words and make double the amount for 4 portions…unless you are serving a small quantity as a side. 
On this delicious and exciting note about the food I am wishing you all a very happy Tuesday 💚♥️💚

Shaved Steak & Asiago Sandwich (15 min prep-to-table)
1. Mince fresh garlic. Add olive oil to pan and roast garlic, leaving slightly raw.
2. Add sliced onions to oil and cook until tender. Salt and pepper. Remove from heat.
3. Add shaved flank steak to pan. Season with garlic, cracked black pepper, and salt. Cook to medium rare. Remove from heat. 
4. Butter sourdough bread. Spread pesto on one side, garlic truffle aioli on the other.
5. Begin frying bread on pan. Add shaved parmesan and Asiago cheese to one side.
6. As cheese starts to melt, add steak and onions on one slice of bread. Top with cheese and close slices.
7. Roast both sides of sandwich equally.
8. Serve with side salad with balsamic vinaigrette and enjoy!

INGREDIENTS
1 tablespoon olive oil
1 medium onion (chopped)
4 medium carrots (peeled and cut into 1/4-inch pieces)
4 ribs celery (chopped)
3 cloves garlic (minced)
1 teaspoon dried oregano
½ teaspoon dried thyme
1 bay leaf
¾ teaspoon salt (or to taste)
¼ teaspoon black pepper
4 cups low sodium chicken broth
4 cups water (or chicken broth)
1 pound boneless, skinless chicken breasts
6 ounces egg noodles
chopped fresh parsley (optional, for serving)

INSTRUCTIONS
Press the sauté button on the Instant Pot and add the olive oil to the pot. Once the pot is hot, add the onion, carrots and celery and cook, stirring occasionally, until veggies start to soften, about 3 minutes. Stir in the garlic.
Press "Cancel" to turn off the Instant Pot.
Add the dried oregano, thyme, bay leaf, salt, pepper, broth and water to the pot. Stir. Nestle the chicken into the broth.
Close the Instant Pot lid and turn the valve to the sealing position. Pressure cook on high pressure for 7 minutes. The Instant Pot will take about 20 minutes to reach pressure and then the cook time will begin counting down.

Why is canned tuna so cheap when fresh tuna is so expensive? 

Tuna salad:
- Tuna+mayo+salt+yogurt+lime
- Red coral lettuce 
- Baby cos lettuce 
- Butterhead lettuce
- Fresh shallots 
- Goji berries 
- Spring onions 
- Hard boiled egg 

Well it basically comes down to what is described as "sushinomics". Tuna that is canned are species that reproduce quickly creating a vast supply (albacore, yellowtail etc.) But are considered less tasty. The ones that are used for sashimi and sushi are the Bluefin tuna which not only require more efforts in catch but are also low in supply. With the fish only reaching reproductive at 8 years and only having a life span of around 40 years, there aren't much to go around. Overfishing has also greatly contributed to the decline in supply of bluefins as they are being caught before being able to reproduce. Lack in regulation will likely lead to extinction of these tasty swimmers. Luckily there are efforts being put forward and the status of bluefin have been reduce from endangered to least concern. Which is great but it needs to be continued because they taste so good 🥺.

Oh and side note: if you dont want to add alot of mayo to your tuna; sub with unsweetened yogurt, lime and salt. Gives it a fresh taste and adds a 'lil probiotics to you diet.

Cajun Ranchero Pork Chops w/ Asparagus

• 8  boneless thin sliced pork chops
• 1 packet ranch seasoning 
• 1 tsp. Pink Himalayan Salt 🧂 
• 2 tsp. Black Pepper 
• 2 tsp. Paprika
• 2 tsp. Garlic Powder 🧄 
• 1 ziplock bag 
• 1 bag steamable asparagus 

- Combine ingredients & shake well

- Refrigerate overnight 

- Set Air Fryer to 380° for 19 minutes

- Turn over at 11 minutes 

- Turn over at 3 minutes (I added 2 minutes for a total of 5 minutes remaining)

- Steam Asparagus as directed (I use steam in bag 4 minutes)
