ASSEMBLE 🍽 DON’T COOK 🤍

Truth, I am not at all a great cook…but I am creative, and I love to cook.

I did not grow up with a refined palate but did have a mother and grandmother who loved to 'bung it together', as my mum Margot would say. And so, as I developed a love for all things food, I had to start by instinct. I must also confess that I'm terribly lazy and am always trying to find the simple route of favourite dishes. Even the most delicious meals I make rarely take more time than they need to. This is why I follow a simple rule. Assemble the dinner, but don't try to cook it.

We're inundated with perfection these days. Scroll through your Instagram and see how many plates of food have the perfect basil leaf cocked on the perfect forkful of pasta. I would be frustrated to create a meal like this; nobody has time for that!

Instead, I don't sweat it. My dinners are platters of messy sauces and imperfectly cut veggies. I will cook grains and throw on top whatever needs to be used up from the veg crisper in my refrigerator. 

I write this story because on the weekend, In an attempt to impress, I went against my rule and attempted to follow a recipe. LOL.. it was a fail. Place me in a bustling environment of chatter and champers, and well… let's just say I am not great at Muti-tasking. I now know never to go against what makes me feel comfortable in my kitchen. 

I chalk my mistakes up to one word: rustic. Instead, I make what feels good to make, what gets my hands dirty, and what shows the season's colours. Instead, I tear basil leaves with my hands and call it a day.

Whether you are a right or left-brain thinker who doesn't (or does) love cooking, no worries… the trick is to assemble, not cook. Simplify, and you will be healthier and less stressed for it.

Ingredients
1.5 lbs boneless skinless chicken breasts cooked and shredded*
2 Tbsp ghee or avocado oil
1 medium butternut squash cut into 3/4” cubes (about 4 cups)
Sea salt and black pepper
1 small yellow onion diced
4 cloves garlic minced
1 red bell pepper diced
1 green bell pepper diced
2 Tbsp fresh jalapeños finely chopped
2 tsp cumin
1 tsp oregano
3/4 tsp chili powder
1/4 tsp chipotle chili powder
4 oz can diced green chiles
3 cups chicken bone broth
1 tbsp fresh minced cilantro
1 tbsp fresh lime juice
2 tbsp nutritional yeast optional
Sea salt and black pepper to taste
Garnish: “sour cream” coconut cream see notes** avocado slices, cilantro

Instructions

If your chicken needs to be cooked and shredded, do this first* and set aside. Prepare all ingredients before beginning.

Heat a large dutch oven over medium heat and add the ghee or oil. Add the butternut squash and sprinkle all over with sea salt and pepper. Sauté, stirring occasionally for about 5 minutes, until just beginning to brown and soften.

Add in the diced onion and sauté for about a minute until translucent. Then, add in the garlic, peppers, jalapeño and spices, stir and sauté for 3 minutes, until fragrant and softened.

On repeat;

Spicy Tuna Pancake/Gochu-Chamchi Jeon!(고추참치전) 

Sharing another easy and tasty dish you can enjoy any day of the week! Recently, you guys may have seen my story photos, I had received a wonderful box of Korean products from @kseafoodusa. It included a nice variety of pantry items from Korea: like roasted seaweed, canned tuna, seaweed crackers, nori sheets and more! Thanks to them I was able to make this delicious jeon!! Recipe below!🤗🤗

Ingredients:
Gochu chamchi (spicy tuna) 1 can 
1/2 c diced onion
1/2 T garlic minced
2T scallion, chopped
3/4 buchim garoo (korean pancake mix)
pinch black pepper

1)Open can and drain tuna for 5-10min 
2)Combine all ingredients into a mixing bowl, without over mixing. 
3)Heat pan and cook jeon until golden brown on both sides, in med low heat. Drop about 2tbsp for each jeon. Makes about 9 pc. total. Enjoy with favorite dipping sauce!! 😋😋

These were super tasty and not fishy at all!! I didn't need to add any salt or seasoning since the canned tuna was already seasoned and had a nice savory kick to it!🤗🤗 

And look for these brands if you want to try some high quality Korean seafood!!👍👍

Cheesy Ancho Queso Sausage and Pasta

Looking for an easy weeknight dish? This Easy Cheesy Ancho Queso Sausage and Pasta 👆🏻is SO yummy, cheesy and has a delicious little kick to it too. 🌶

Featuring the Ancho Queso Chicken Sausage from @gilbertscraftsausages, you are definitely going to want to ✨SAVE✨ this #recipe for later this week, or next! It's a great one to have in your recipe arsenal! 🙌🏻

WHAT YOU NEED:
🧀 12 ounces elbow pasta (we used @eatgoodwheat), 3 tbsp unsalted butter, 3 tbsp flour, 1 tsp sweet paprika, 1/2 tsp onion powder, 1/4 tsp garlic powder, 24 ounces evaporated milk, 2 cups shredded cheddar cheese plus about 1/4 cup more for topping, 1/4 cup parmesan cheese, 1 package (4 links) Gilbert's Ancho Queso Chicken Sausages, 1/4 cup panko breadcrumbs, 2 tbsp butter (melted), and chopped chives as desired

HOW YOU MAKE IT:
🧀 Start off by pre-heating your oven to 375 degrees.
🧀 Cook elbows according to package directions. Drain and set aside.
🧀 While pasta cooks, coin sausage links and then sauté in pan over medium heat for a couple of minutes, until slightly browned. Remove from heat and set aside.
🧀 In a large pot, melt butter. Then whisk in: flour, paprika, onion and garlic powders. Cook for 1- 2 min.
🧀 Next, whisk in milk, a little at a time. Cook until sauce begins to thicken. Then, remove from heat.
🧀 Stir in only 2 cups cheddar cheese as well as parmesan.
🧀 Add in pasta and stir to combine. Then add in sausage coins and again, stir to coat.
🧀 Transfer macaroni mixture to a pan (we used a 9.5 x 9.5 square) and sprinkle with remaining 1/4 cup shredded cheddar cheese. Set aside.
🧀 Combine breadcrumbs and melted butter. Then sprinkle coated breadcrumbs over top of the cheese.
🧀 Bake at 375 degrees for 20- 25 minutes. Once done, remove from oven.
🧀 Garnish with chives and enjoy!

Look for these Ancho Queso Chicken Sausages next time you’re at @target! 🎯🛒

Macro Friendly Chicken Enchiladas 🥑 

Ingredients:
Whipped FF cream cheese, 80 g
Salsa Verde, 60 g (1/4 cup)
1 Tbs lime juice
1 tsp chili powder
1/2 tsp cumin
1/2 tsp onion powder
1/2 tsp garlic powder
1/3 cup cilantro
Green onions, as much as desired
2 cups shredded chicken (Any kind you want! Great if you have leftovers from a different night. In this photo, I used an HEB rotisserie chicken!)
10 extra thin mission corn tortillas
1 can red enchilada sauce
3 oz lite Mexican cheese

Directions:
(1) Mix your cream cheese, salsa verde, lime juice, and all the seasonings together. Add in cilantro, green onions, & shredded/diced chicken. Combine.

(2) Warm your corn tortillas in the microwave for 10 to 15 seconds until flexible. Divide the chicken and cream cheese mixture evenly amongst the 10 tortillas. Place them seem side down in a greased baking dish.

(3) Cover the enchiladas with the sauce & shredded cheese. Bake it for 25 for about 10-15 min. 

Serve hot! The guacamole shown is not included in the macros but it’s highly encouraged as an add-on 😘.

Macros per Enchilada:
Cals: 168
Protein: 15.1
Carbs: 19.2
Fat: 3.4

YOU ARE ALLOWED TO EAT LARGE PORTIONS 🍝

Understanding portion sizes can be really difficult as most of us learn this in our formative years from our parents. Unless you seek formal education yourself, you’re more than likely to continue on with what you’ve been taught. On top of that, 
diet culture and the media certainly influence us to believe that smaller portions = healthier. All of which neglects the most important part, NUTRIENTS. Irrespective of portion size, if your meal consistently lacks key nutrients or fails to fuel your body, then it’s irrelevant. 

Now, I will say this. YES portion size matters when looking at weight loss and fitness / macro goals. 🏃🏽‍♀️

YES you can have a portion size that is too large if it makes you feel too full and uncomfortable. 🤢

YES you can have a portion size that is too small. E.g. if you’re left feeling hungry after eating (not enough food or enough calorie / nutrient dense foods) 🤕

Key messages 🔑
- eat to fuel your body 
- listen to your hunger cues 
- ensure your plate has adequate nutrients

Miso butter noodles with nasturtiums and garden greens ❤ is a quick meal my family loves.  #onepotmeal #onepotmeals #healthynotboring 
#easymeals
Just cook spaghetti (or your favorite noodle) , steaming diced sweet potatoes or squash cubes above the same pot till tender. In a bowl,  whisk 1Tbsp miso per portion with some pasta water. 
Wash greens in colander,  strain pasta over those greens to wilt them.  Add back to pot, stirring in steamed squash/yams and miso paste. Finish by adding a big dollop of butter and garnish with flowers or herbs. Shave parm if you like.  Loosen sauce with reserved pasta water and add more miso to season as needed.

Let talk easy peasy meals! Last week was a write off for me and meal prepping. First week back from vaca and I needed to get back into the groove of things! ​​​​​​​​
​​​​​​​​
This is one of my go to meal prep recipes! Super simple and quick! I always precut the broccoli and precook the quinoa and shrimp (or chicken), which will be good in the fridge for 3 days. ​​​​​​​​
​​​​​​​​
- 1 cup of broccoli​​​​​​​​
- 6-8 shrimps​​​​​​​​
- 1/3 or 1/2 cup of quinoa​​​​​​​​
- Coconut Oil (or any oil you have)​​​​​​​​
- Spices of your choice (I use Peg City Seasoning from Spice World and chili powder) ​​​​​​​​
​​​​​​​​
Put a bit of oil in a pan and add the broccoli, I usually add a lid to cook a bit faster.​​​​​​​​
After about 5 minutes and stirring between, add the shrimp (may need a bit more oil to not stick).​​​​​​​​
Stir in between and add quinoa after about 3 minutes.​​​​​​​​
Add spices - I don't measure, just go by taste.​​​​​​​​
Mix it all up to get the spices over everything and heat the quinoa.​​​​​​​​
Put it in a bowl, and time to eat! ​​​​​​​​
​​​​​​​​
Would you try this recipe?? ​​​​​​​​
​​​​​​​​
Let me know if you try it, and what you think!!​​​​​​​​

HEALTHY & EASY BANANA BREAD MUFFINS🍌🧁

I’ve recently injured my knee again and currently I’m baking as a way to cope. These muffins took less then 30 minutes and I’m not ashamed to say these will be gone by tonight:.)

Ingredients:
2 ripe bananas, mashed 
1/3 cup olive oil 
1/2 cup maple syrup 
2 eggs 
1/2 tsp vanilla 

2 cups flour 
1/2 tsp baking powder 
1 tsp baking soda 
1/2 tsp salt 

Preheat oven to 350
Add the wet ingredients to a bowl and mix. In a separate bowl add the dry ingredients and mix. Then, fold the dry mixture into the wet until everything is combined. Add muffin liners to a muffin pan or grease your muffin tins, and pour the batter to at least half way full (mine made 11). Bake for 25 minutes and enjoy:)

Chili Chargrilled Corn & Mushrooms Salad 
.
Delicious chargrilled flavors with some sweet corn and meaty mushrooms: this meat free salad is balanced, complete, colorful and healthy. Summer in a plate, ideal for a weeknight! 
—— 
⏱: 15 minutes 
——
Serves 2 
INGREDIENTS
* 2 corn on the cob, kernels cut off 
* 4 big flat mushrooms, sliced 
* 20g jalapeño pepper’s slices 
* 1 avocado
* 2 tsp green Tabasco 
* 100g rocket salad 
* 1 tbsp olive oil 
* Dressing: 
 * 1 tbsp Dijon mustard
 * 1 tbsp honey 
 * 1 tbsp cider vinegar
 * 1 tbsp olive oil 
 * 2 garlic cloves, crushed 
——
METHOD
Heat 1 tbsp of olive oil on a griddle pan, on medium heat, then sear the mushrooms slices on these for 5 minutes on each side.
In the meantime, in a non sticky frying pan, chargrill the corn kernels on medium heat, tossing firmly and regularly to ensure homogeneous cooking and coloring. (Should take 8-10 minutes)
Plate the salad, top with the corn, add the avocado, drizzle the Tabasco on the avocado, lay the mushrooms and jalapeño slices, drizzle the dressing all over and serve while still lukewarm.

I've been LOVING having overnight oats for breakfast lately. 😋 They're so quick and easy to make and they last up to five days in the fridge (so you can meal prep breakfast for the week)! 😍 Plus, there are endless things you can add to them so you never get tired of eating the same thing!

Here's a recipe for my go-to flavor at the moment...

Super easy blueberry overnight oats!

Ingredients:
- ⅔ cup rolled oats
- ⅔ cup milk, of your choice
- ½ cup vanilla greek yogurt
- ½ teaspoon vanilla extract
- 1 teaspoon chia seed, optional
- ½ teaspoon cinnamon
- 2 teaspoons of something sweet like honey, berry jam, or maple syrup
- handful of fresh blueberries

Directions:
1. In a mason jar or sealable container, add the oats, milk, yogurt, vanilla extract, chia seeds, cinnamon and blueberries and stir together.
2. Seal and place in the refrigerator overnight for up to five days.
3. Top with your something sweet and blueberries.
4. Give it a good stir and enjoy! 🤗

• OVEN BAKED CHICKEN PASANDA •

Let’s hear it for the creamy curry’s in the back 📣 This was such a fantastic simple dinner which hit all the right warming belly spots!🥺

* INGREDIENTS *
- Chicken Breast Fillets (I used 300g for 2 portions)
- 1 tbsp Cumin 
- 1 tbsp Medium Curry Powder
- 1 tsp Ground Coriander 
- 1 tsp Turmeric 
- 2 tbsp Ground Almonds 
- 250ml Chicken Stock 
- 3 tbsp Light Soft Cheese 

* METHOD *
- Coat the chicken in all spices and ground almond. 
- Put chicken into an oven proof dish and cover with dissolved chicken stock. 
- Cook at around 180 degrees for 1 hour. 
- Remove from the oven and mix in the soft cheese and sprinkle over more ground almond. 
- Cook for a further 30 minutes until sauce has thickened and ground almond has browned. 

Served with a side of Basmati Rice and enjoy! 

A perfect meal to start the week that ticks the balanced healthy meal box and hits those good macros - if that’s your thing!

🌶️🍝🍅 CHILLI BUTTER TOMATO SPAGHETTI 🍅🍝🌶️ Long time no pasta, so just dropping by with a taste of the Med right here 🤤🤤 A fresh tomato sauce, simmered with garlic and chilli, lotttts of butter, and served with fresh pasta. So much flavour with (mostly) store cupboard ingredients, and ready in 20 - perfect for summer evenings ☀️☀️ I like mine extra saucy and extra buttery, so feel free to bump up your ingredients to suit your taste 👌🏼👌🏼

Chilli Butter Tomato Spaghetti (serves 2):

150g spaghetti
50g unsalted butter
1/2 red onion, finely chopped
350g cherry/baby plum tomatoes, halved
2 x garlic cloves, sliced
1/2 x teaspoon sea salt (may need more, adjust to taste)
1/2 x teaspoon chilli flakes
1 x tablespoon apple cider vinegar (I used @willysacv)
1/2 teaspoon sugar
Freshly cracked black pepper
Small handful parsley, chopped
50g Parmesan, grated

Cook spaghetti according to pack instructions. Save a ladle of pasta water for the sauce.

On a medium high heat, add the butter to a large saucepan and gently fry the onions for 2-3 minutes. Add the tomato halves and fry for 4-5 minutes. Add the garlic, ACV, sugar, salt, chilli, and continue to cook until the tomatoes soften and release their juices (about another 5-10 minutes). Squish the tomatoes with the back of a wooden spoon to break apart. Add enough reserved pasta water to loosen the sauce (about 50ml), the cooked spaghetti, half the parmesan and the parsley, and combine well. Season with pepper, more salt if required, and serve with the remaining parmesan on top 👌🏼👌🏼

اكلة فلسطينية رهيبة و مش كتير صعبة 🙂
الطريقة:
- نقشر البصل و نقطعه قطع متوسطة الحجم
- في مقلاة ، نضع كمية وافرة من زيت الزيتون و المازولا ثم نضيف البصل و نضع ملح ، بهار و عندما يقرب من النضج نضيف له سماق
- نحضر قطع دجاج و ننظفها ثم نضع عليها قليل من الخل و ملح و فلفل و بهارات الدجاج و بابريكا و نضعها في صينية في الفرن و تترك حتى تنضج (ممكن سلقها ثم تحميرها لكن الطريقة الاولى ألذ)
- نحضر رغيف خبز مخصص للمسخن (سميك شوي) و ندهنه بقليل من مرق البصل و الماء (او مرق الدجاج) ثم نضع البصل فوقه ثم لوز محمص و الدجاج و نرش عليه سماق

☆☆ Palestinian Musakhan ☆☆ very delicious meal and not very hard 🙂
- Peel the onions and cut them as medium sized pieces

- Use a special bread for musakhan (little thick) and add on its surface little of onion soup and water (or chicken soup) then add the onion, roasted almonds, chicken pieces and spray it with sumac

🥘 Not the prettiest of meals but I seriously fancied comfort food tonight after a not too successful trip to my consultant. 

🧯 I just think comfort food isn’t suited to warm weather really but fortunately I remembered this one pot that I haven’t made in forever!

🍗 Pop a free range chicken and a selection of veg (I used potatoes, onions, carrots, swede and leeks) into a heavy casserole. Smother the chicken with butter and plenty of salt and pepper. Add a couple of glasses of white wine and water, stash a lid on and pop into the oven for about an hour. 

🥄 Give the chicken a quick baste with the juices and then back in the oven without the lid for 20 mins/half an hour until the skin is crisp and golden.

🔪 Carve the chicken into thick slices and serve in bowls with the veg and spoonfuls of the broth and a sprinkle of parsley.

🥣 If you have any leftover broth,  veg and chicken, you could whizz it into a quick soup. But I never have because we never have any leftovers. 🤷‍♂️

STUFFED POTATO SKINS 🥔🥓🧀 

Wow, these were incredible and so filling - I got the recipe Inspo from my girl @slimming_teganxx page ❤️

Ingredients (1 portion):
- 1 large potato (mine was 330g)
- 1/2 onion
- 2 bacon rashers
- 50g sweetcorn
- 30g low fat cream cheese
- 30g low fat cheese
- Spring onion & parsley to serve

Method (45 mins ish):

1. Pierce the potato with a knife in serval place and pop your potato in the microwave for 10 mins, then wrap in foil with a few sprays of oil and put in the oven/airfryer for 20-30mins

2. Meanwhile in a pan cook your onions and bacon, once cooked add to a mixing bowl with the sweetcorn and cream cheese 

3. Once the potato is cooked, cut in half and scoop out the middle and put in the mixing bowl, mix everything together then scoop back into the skins

4. Top with cheese and put back in the oven/ under the grill until melted, serve with some spring onions & parsley 

I served with the rainbow salad from @aldiuk with a tbsp of @aldiuk Caesar dressing (see pic 3)

Total calories for skins approx. 620
Total calories in meal approx. 690

Chorizo and mozzarella gnocchi 🤩 

Serves 3 big portions/ 4 smaller ones

~ 1 red onion chopped into dices
~ 3 garlic cloves 
~ 100g diced chorizo 
~ 400g tin chopped tomatoes 
~ 500g gnocchi 
~ 75g grated mozzarella 
~ salt & pepper 

Fry the onions and chorizo in a pan until the onions soften around 5-7 minutes 
Add the garlic cloves and fry for a further 2 minutes 
Pour in the tin of chopped tomatoes and stir - season if necessary 
Bring to a simmer then add the gnocchi and stir it all together. Cook this all for around 8-10 minutes. 
Pour the contents of the pan into oven proof dish, top with mozzarella and put under the grill for 5 minutes or until golden 😋

Around 500 cals for 3 portions but to make it lower you could use a ‘lighter’ mozzarella

Creamy broccoli in garlic parmesan sauce
.
Poate să fie sidedish sau fel principal.
E atât de bun și simplu cu o coajă de pâine lângă.
Are bucăți crocante de bacon iar despre sos nu vreau să vă zic decât că e divin. Restul vorbim după ce îl faceți.
.
Eu așa am făcut :
Am gătit întâi în tigaie nonaderentă bacon (de fapt am avut pancetta) tăiat cubulețe.
Până s-a rumenit frumos. Fără ulei, fără nimic. Lasă el destulă grăsime.
Apoi l-am scos pe hârtie absorbantă.
.
Mi-am tocat o ceapă albă și 4 căței usturoi.
Am șters tigaia de grăsimea de la pancetta și am pus un cub mic de unt.
Am pus și ceapa și am lăsat câteva minute până s-a înmuiat puțin. Nu prăjim.
Am adăugat buchețele de broccoli (de la 1 broccoli măricel) și am asezonat cu sare și piper. Am gătit câteva minute și am adăugat și cățeii de usturoi tocați.
După încă 2 minute am adăugat puțină apă.
Apoi a venit rândul a 400 ml smântână de gătit amestecată cu o linguriță rasă amidon alimentar.
Foc mic. Gustăm. Adăugăm sare dacă mai este nevoie.
După ce s-a îngroșat puțin, (aprx 7 minute) aducem și pancetta crocantă în tigaie și amestecăm să se contopească aromele.
.
Oprim focul. Radem niște mozzarella și niște parmezan (cam 50 grame de fiecare) și dăm la cuptorul încins bine la funcția grill. Să rumenim ușor preparatul și să topim brânzele alea.😋
Câteva minute.
.
Niște ceapă verde tocată nu ar strica... Și nici puțin busuioc sau ce altă verdeață v-ar plăcea...
.
Este un deliciu și îi rog pe neiubitorii de broccoli să îl încerce și așa.
.
.
.
.

.
.
.
.
.
.
.

.
.

Tempura is a typical Japanese dish that is super versatile. The most well-known dishes are prawns and vegetables in tempura batter🍤. The batter is made in a snap with just flour, corn starch, salt, egg and ice-cold water. 

Did you know that the ice-cold water makes the dish lovely and crispy and it also absorbs less fat🥶? 

Go on a journey to Japan and don't forget to save this recipe for later!

𝗜͟𝗻͟𝗴͟𝗿͟𝗲͟𝗱͟𝗶͟𝗲͟𝗻͟𝘁͟𝘀
For the dipping sauce: 
175 ml dashi stock 
2 tablespoons soy sauce 
2 tablespoons mirin (Japanese sweet wine) 

For the batter: 
60 g all-purpose flour 
60 g cornstarch 
1 teaspoon kosher salt 
1 large egg, beaten 
175 ml ice-cold club soda 

For frying: 
300 g thinly sliced vegetables 
12 large shrimp, peeled and deveined with tail on 
Vegetable, canola, or peanut oil 

For serving: 
400 g cooked Jasmine rice 

𝗣͟𝗿͟𝗲͟𝗽͟𝗮͟𝗿͟𝗮͟𝘁͟𝗶͟𝗼͟𝗻
Step 1. 
Make the dipping sauce - In a small bowl, whisk together dashi stock, soy sauce, and mirin. Set aside. 

Step 2.
Make the batter - In a medium bowl, stir together flour, cornstarch, and salt. Pour in beaten egg and club soda and stir with chopsticks to combine evenly. Batter will be lumpy. Refrigerate batter till ready to use. 

Step 3. 
Prep for frying - Fill a wok or deep pot halfway with oil and place over medium-high heat. Place a wire rack over a sheet pan lined with paper towels. Heat oil to 190°C or test oil by dropping in a bit of batter. If it sizzles vigorously but doesn’t brown too quickly you’re good to go. 

Step 4.
Fry the tempura - Gently dip vegetables and shrimp in tempura and lower into oil. Fry in small batches to avoid overcrowding. Flip and separate items while frying until batter is crisp and golden brown, about 1 to 1 1/2 minutes. Transfer to wire rack. Allow oil to reheat between batches. 

Step 5.
Serve and enjoy - Divide tempura and rice between four individual plates and serve with a side of dipping sauce.

Quand il s'agit de fitness et d'atteindre vos objectifs, il est bon de comprendre l'essence de la perte de graisse corporelle, tout en augmentant votre masse musculaire. 💪🏼

C'est ce qui vous donnera ce look défini et tonique que vous recherchez si vous connaissez les bonnes étapes et la façon de les exécuter correctement.✅

Si vous trouvez que c'est un défi et que vous avez l'impression de n'arriver à rien, il existe des moyens simples pour perdre la graisse, et gagner du muscle :

✨ Assurez-vous que vous donnez la priorité à votre récupération. Cela signifie boire beaucoup d'eau, se rafraîchir après les séances d'entraînement avec des étirements et/ou des rouleaux de mousse, et prendre suffisamment de repos de qualité la nuit.

✨ Mangez des protéines maigres avec la majorité de vos repas. Les protéines sont responsables de la réparation des muscles et vous aident à brûler des calories sans stocker de graisse supplémentaire.

✨ Essayez d'être plus actif pendant la journée. Qu'il s'agisse de marcher davantage plutôt que de prendre les escaliers et de conduire, ou de faire un peu de yoga pendant votre pause, c'est toujours un bonus d'utiliser plus d'énergie plutôt que de la stocker.

✨ Mangez des macros dans les bonnes proportions. Le suivi de votre consommation est important car c'est la bonne consommation qui va aider à la perte de graisse, à l'énergie et au maintien.

✨ Stimulez la croissance musculaire avec un entraînement en résistance. L'entraînement par résistance est la meilleure forme d'entraînement lorsqu'il s'agit de gain musculaire et de perte de graisse.

Devenir maigre et en bonne santé peut être facile avec le bon coach et les bons outils.🥗

Чоколадни колач

Или колач из вртича или црнац без јаја, како вам драже 😁

Помешати 210г брашна, 2 кашичице какаоа и 2 кашичице соде бикарбоне. Додати кесицу ванилин шећера и 170г кристал шећера, промешати суве састојке.
Додавати 400мл јогурта и миксером умутити, затим додати 100мл уља и наставити мутити миксером да смеса буде без грудвица.
Сипати у тепсију, моја је већа да колач не би био висок, пећи 30 минута у загрејаној рерни на 200степени.
Док се пече направити прелив, у шерпицу сипати 6 кашика шећера и 100мл млека, оставити да проври.
Чим проври додати 100г маслаца/маргарина и 100г црне чоколаде, оставити на шпорету да се сви састојци истопе.
Склонити са шпорета и поклопити да остане топло.
Када је колач печен, исећи на коцке док је врућ и одмах прелити топлим преливом.
Оставити да се охлади и сервирати.

**Spoiler alert : contains courgette recipe**

It's that time of year again.  Too many courgettes = hunt for new recipes🔍🤦🏻‍♀️

Found this one in a Turkish recipe book in the local library. Easy to make & really tasty so thought we'd share. 

Courgette Fritters (makes c. 10 fritters)
Ingredients
400g courgette, trimmed and coarsely grated
½ tsp salt
2 tbsp olive oil
½ onion, finely chopped
1 garlic clove, finely chopped
55g plain flour, sifted
½ tsp baking powder
1½ eggs, lightly beaten
115g feta cheese, crumbled
5g flat-leaf parsley, chopped
Greek-style yoghurt, to serve

Instructions
Place the grated courgette in a colander, sprinkle with the salt and toss to mix. Set aside for 20 mins. 
Heat 1 tbsp of olive oil in a large frying pan over a medium heat. Add the onion and the garlic and cook for 6-7 minutes, until softened. Remove as much liquid as possible from the grated courgette by squeezing it with your hands, then add it to the pan to cook, stirring for another 4-5 minutes, or until the courgette starts to colour (our courgettes didn’t really colour but the end result was still delicious). Remove from the heat to a large bowl and allow to cool slightly. 
Add the flour, baking powder, egg, feta and parsley to the bowl and stir well. Season. 
Heat the remaining olive oil in a clean non-stick pan over a medium heat. Cook heaped tablespoons of the courgette mixture, in batches, for 3-4 minutes on each side, or until deep golden. Drain well on paper towels before serving with the yoghurt. 
 
From a Turkish recipe book by Leanne Kitchen.
